title: sandman cookies(or no bake)
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan, then add sugar, cocoa and milk and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla; stir.
Put on wax paper by teaspoon.
Let cool.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in microwave or double boiler.

Add peanut butter and almonds which have been toasted with a brushing of margarine. Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper and let set. This makes a large batch which can be frozen for an indefinite period.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, then add Italian dressing and chill 1/2 hour. Add mayo, olives, onions, salt, pepper and cheese.
Chill until needed.

title: 3 cheese and carrot tart
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 9-inch pie dish with 1 tablespoon oil.
Rinse shredded potatoes and squeeze dry in a kitchen towel. Place potatoes in dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and toss to blend.
Spread in a layer over the bottom of the dish and bake 25 minutes until browned.
Reduce heat to 375°.
Heat remaining oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add carrots and onion and cook, stirring frequently until softened, about 3 minutes.
Whisk eggs, cottage cheese, milk, Swiss cheese, salt, pepper and parsley in mixing bowl.
Add carrots and onion.
Pour over potato crust and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes, until puffed and lightly browned.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Cut lemon in thin slices.
Place in a bowl and cover with sugar.
Mash thoroughly until all juice is extracted.
Add water. Let stand 1 hour.
Allow 1 or 2 tablespoons of the strained lemon juice for each serving.
Pour into glass filled with shaved ice and fill with water.
Garnish with maraschino cherry and slice of lemon.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: heavenly punch
directions: Mix everything together and freeze in Tupperware.
Thaw until slushy and add 2 bottles ginger ale.

title: spaghetti with oil and garlic
directions: Cook the spaghetti in a large pot of salted boiling water. Drain.
In a small skillet, heat the oil.
Add the garlic and quickly saute until garlic begins to brown.
Place spaghetti in a serving bowl.
Add the garlic and oil; toss.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: texas fried okra
directions: In a plastic bag,
combine
corn
meal, flour, salt and pepper.
Cut okra into
1/2-inch slices and pour buttermilk or milk over okra and toss.
Place okra in plastic bag and shake. In a skillet, heat oil
and
add
okra.
Fry on moderate heat, turning frequently, until crispy
and
brown.
Drain
on paper towels.
Serve immediately.

title: sour milk yeast rolls
directions: Mix sour milk with soda.
Add sugar, salt and the softened yeast.
Add well beaten egg and margarine.
Add enough flour to make a firm dough.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise in warm place until double.
Punch dough down and shape into small balls.
Place in greased baking pan 1 inch apart.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake in 425° oven for 20-25 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put milk, rice, sugar, lemon rind and salt in pot and simmer approximately 1 hour.
When rice is cooked, remove from stove and add the eggs, sugar and vanilla which have been mixed together. Stir constantly for 2 minutes.
Pour into serving dish and cool. When cool, refrigerate.

title: green stuff
directions: Combine ingredients until well mixed.
Pour into a container.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Place cooked ham on bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Spread 2 cups cheese over ham. Add cooked noodles over mixture.
Add cream of mushroom soup mixed with 1 can of milk.
Put remaining cheese over top and bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour in greased baking pan and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: quick chocolate fudge(2 pounds)
directions: Put chocolate pieces, broken candy bar, Marshmallow Creme, butter and nuts into bowl.
Combine evaporated milk and sugar in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to boil; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and pour over other ingredients. Stir until chocolate has melted and mixture is smooth and glossy. Pour in ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Whip cream cheese with milk.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, except crackers and cheese.
Place in ungreased 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with topping (crackers and cheese).
Bake, uncovered, in oven until cheese is melted.

title: marinated, browned beef tips (stew beef)
directions: Prepare marinade of red wine vinegar, red wine (optional), balsamic vinegar, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce (optional). Cut stew beef/chuck steak into 1-inch cubes. Marinate in the marinade for at least 4 hours, overnight in refrigerator if possible, in non-metallic container. Light coat marinated beef tips in "flour mixture" and brown over medium-high heat. After browned, add residual marinade and cook until it forms a thick sauce.

title: banana boat
directions: Prepare mix as package directs for pudding. Fold in Cool Whip, miniature marshmallows and banana slices.
Line bottom and sides of a 10 x 6-inch baking dish with wafers.
Pour in pudding mixture. Garnish as desired.

title: picante pot roast
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, brown meat in oil.
Drain. Sprinkle onions over meat.
Combine tomato sauce, picante sauce, cumin, oregano and garlic.
Pour over meat and onions.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer gently about 2 to 2 1/2 hours, adding green pepper during last 15 minutes of cooking.
Begin checking meat for tenderness after 1 hour and 45 minutes of cooking.
Remove meat to serving platter; keep warm.

title: oyster stew
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup oyster liquid.	Season oysters with salts and peppers; frizzle in their own juice until slightly curled.	Set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour; blend.
Add onions; stir until onions are cooked.
Add oyster liquid.
Add milk 1 cup at a time, stirring constantly.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Add oysters.
Check for additional seasoning.
Sprinkle onion on top just before serving.
Serves 6-8.

title: fried spinach balls
directions: Beat egg and set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients. Refrigerate until cold.
Shape into balls; roll in crumbs, then in beaten egg.
Deep fry in fat until brown.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: frito salad
directions: Mix beans, tomatoes, pepper and onion in a large bowl.
Right before serving, add corn chips and toss with dressing.

title: party rolls
directions: Slice each roll several times and put on platter.
Looks very pretty and tastes delicious.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in a large pan over water.
Stir in peanuts.
Add noodles and mix.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper. Makes about 30.

title: golden raisin buns
directions: Combine water, butter, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Heat to boil.
Add flour all at once, then over low heat beat with wooden spoon about 1 minute or until a smooth, thick dough.
Remove from heat.
Continue beating 2 minutes to cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each until mixture has satiny sheen. Stir in raisins.
Drop heaping measuring tablespoons about 2 inches apart on greased sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until doubles.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool.
While still warm, spread frosting.
Makes 20.

title: home-made waffles
directions: Beat whites till stiff.
Mix other ingredients and fold into whites.
Cook.

title: watergate salad
directions: Work fast and mix everything together. Add Cool Whip last. Refrigerate and serve.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Mix all ingredients, except avocado and Doritos.
Heat in a large pot (do not boil).

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Grease 2 10 inch pie plates and put sweetened fruit on bottom.
cover with the above mixture and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Use 2 deep dish pie plates.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch casserole or cake pan (or large bowl), shred lettuce.
Then
add
the
rest of the ingredients in the order listed.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Cook beef for 2 1/2 hours, adding water as needed.
When the beef is tender, drain and shred. Add remaining ingredients and heat. Serve on a bun. Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Makes 2 regular loaves.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: summer squash surprise
directions: Slice squash and cook with onion (just to crisp; drain, if necessary).
Mix chicken soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Melt butter and pour over 1/2 package of dressing.
Save some to sprinkle on top.
Place dressing in bottom of casserole dish.
Add squash and onions.
Top with sour cream mixture. Sprinkle with reserved dressing and Parmesan cheese, if desired. Bake at 350° until hot through.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: jewish apple coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except apples together in a large bowl and beat for 10 minutes on medium speed.
Grease tube pan.
Put 1 layer of batter, then one layer of apples and repeat this by making the top layer batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Last 1/2 hour, cover with foil.

title: orange date cake
directions: Mix together, sugar, flour, salt and soda.
Add melted butter, buttermilk and eggs.
Mix well and stir in pecans, dates and orange rind.
Pour into tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: andrea's pie crust(makes 1 pie)
directions: Work Crisco into flour, then sprinkle tap water over this and work in with a fork.
When moist enough, ball up in a wax paper and set aside and let set at least 1 minute or longer.
This can be refrigerated for sometime, then roll out on floured board.
Turn over and roll again.
Roll thin.

title: german sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Pour sugar over shredded cabbage and let stand for several minutes.
Combine other ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil. Pour boiling mixture over cabbage; let stand overnight before using.
This will keep for at least 10 days.
Store in a covered dish, but not a metal container.
This is very good with ham for a buffet dinner.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Don't overbake!

title: strawberry orange delight
directions: In medium bowl stir boiling water and jello together for at least 2 minutes. Stir in cold water. Refrigerate about 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened. Reserve a few oranges for garnish if desired. Gently stir in remaining oranges into thickened gelatin. In a separate bowl beat cream cheese and sugar with a wire whisk until well blended. Gently stir in 2 c. whipped topping. Spoon into large serving bowl, cover with gelatin mixture. Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm. Garnish with remaining whipped topping and reserved oranges.

title: dirt
directions: Grind up the package of Oreos and set aside.
Combine the cream cheese, powdered sugar and the butter.
Cream together and set aside.
Combine the milk, Cool Whip and pudding mixes in a large bowl and mix together.
Add in the cream cheese mixture and stir until there are no lumps.
Starting with the pudding mixture, layer it into a flower pot looking bowl, then put a layer of the Oreos to cover the pudding.
Alternate back and forth and make sure that the Oreos end up on top and place artificial flowers in it.

title: banan-za bread
directions: Warm honey and oil in a saucepan until easily blended. Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk and add to the honey and oil mixture.
Beat eggs and add, in order, the remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: yummy pecans
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Gradually add vanilla and brown sugar.
Fold in pecans by hand and coat well.
Place on cookie sheet with pecan bottoms flat side down.
Bake at 225° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry cream cheese
directions: Mix ingredients, using fork to cut margarine into mixture. Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool before adding cream mixture.

title: mini meat balls
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and 1/8 teaspoon each:
pepper, sage and thyme.
Shape firmly into 6 mini meat loaves in a skillet.
Brown loaves in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Stir in remaining soup and seasoning and water.
Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done. Stir occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: lemonade
directions: Squeeze the juice from 4 of the lemons, limes and oranges; pour into a gallon container.
Thinly slice the remaining fruit and set aside for garnish.
Add water and sugar to juices and mix well.
Chill garnish and serve on ice with fruit slice garnish.

title: cold green beans
directions: Boil beans.
Stir 1/2 teaspoon sugar and salt while boiling. Cook 5 to 7 minutes; leave crispy.
Drain under cold water. Combine shallot, vinegar and salt.
Drizzle in olive oil; add beans and cilantro and toss to coat.
Sprinkle sesame seed on top.

title: cherry-o cheesecake
directions: Mix cheese, milk, juice and vanilla; mix well! Pour into a graham cracker crust and top with cherries. Refrigerate.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Saute until tender in 1 stick butter.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Melt other stick of butter and mix with crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle buttered cracker crumbs over onions and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Mix well, bake at 350° until done.

title: german cheese cake
directions: Place ingredients in order given in large mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer, start on low, move to medium and finish 10 minutes on high.
Batter should be smooth and liquid.
Grease and flour a round 10-inch baking pan 3-inches high; pour into pan and bake 1 hour in preheated 350° oven.
Leave cake in oven with door closed for 1 additional hour after heat is off.
Cool on rack in refrigerator.
Makes 20 servings.

title: chocolate mocha pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Bring cocoa, coffee, salt, sugar, milk and cold water to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add gelatin.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Beat the cooked mixture until smooth.
Beat cream.
Add vanilla.
Fold whipped cream into cooked mixture.
Pour into pie shell and top with nuts or shredded chocolate chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add the other five ingredients and mix well.
Nuts or raisins can be added.
Pour in greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes two loaves.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pie crust) together.
Place in a 10-inch pie plate.
Place top crust on.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then slice.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix filling ingredients in the order given.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for 45 minutes to one hour or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean. Cool before serving.
Makes two pies.

title: drumstick torte
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, 2/3 cup peanuts and butter.
Put in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange a layer of potatoes, layer of onion and another layer of potatoes in casserole.
Mix water and cream of mushroom soup; pour over layers of onion and potatoes.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: honey ham
directions: Fry ham in bouillon soup until brown on one side.
Turn over and add honey on top of ham.
Continue to add enough bouillon soup to keep it from being dry.
Add coffee at the end of cooking. When all is done, there should be a brown sauce for top of ham.

title: russian tea
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot and let heat until almost to a boil.

title: e-z georgia jambalaya(mild)
directions: Cut chicken and sausage into small pieces; lightly brown and set aside.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel, quarter and core apples.
Wrap each piece in a roll. Press dough around apple to seal. Bring to a boil.
Mix orange juice, sugar and butter.
Place dumplings in ovenproof dish.
Pour juice mixture over dumplings and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve with vanilla ice cream.
It's delicious!

title: salsa
directions: In large saucepan bring all ingredients to a boil, simmer for 15 minutes.
Add 6 Tbsp. cornstarch mixed in water.
Continue cooking until desired thickness.
Will thicken more after cooled. (Can in hot water bath for 20 minutes).

title: turtle stew 1
directions: Boil the turtle meat for 20 minutes.
Melt butter in a pot and cook the sliced garlic until browned.
Coat the cooked turtle meat with flour and add it to the pot along with the onion.
Cook the meat until browned.
Pour in the stock in which the turtle was boiled.
Simmer for several hours or until the meat is tender. Add potatoes, stir in the soup and cook an additional 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: About 40 minutes before serving cut half of cheese into 6 slices; shred remaining cheese.
Make a 2 1/2-inch horizontal cut in meatier part of each chicken breast half to make a deep pocket. Place 1 slice of cheese in each.
On waxed paper, combine flour and salt.
In bowl, mix egg and milk; on another sheet of waxed paper place cornmeal.
Dip each chicken breast into flour, egg mixture and then in cornmeal.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, brown chicken on both sides about 5 minutes; remove to plate.
To same skillet, add salsa, taco sauce and 1/3 cup water over high heat, heat to boiling.
Arrange chicken in sauce, reduce heat to low, simmer uncovered 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and cook until cheese melts.
Serves 6.
Has 480 calories per serving, 22 grams fat, 147 mg. cholesterol and 1405 mg. sodium.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Boil cranberries in 2 quarts water for 20 minutes.
Boil the sugar, water and cinnamon for 30 minutes.
Strain cranberries and combine juice with the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: watermelon sherbet
directions: Put plastic wrap in bottom of bowl.
Smash lime sherbet on bottom and sides (rind).
Soften raspberry sherbet and mix with chocolate chips (fruit and seeds).
Put mixture in middle of bowl. Cover with plastic; freeze.
Turn upside down.
Put warm rag on bottom of bowl, remove bowl and slice.
Use warm water to dip knife for slices.

title: moro de frijoles(rice and beans cooked together)
directions: Clean and wash rice.
Set aside.
Mix bacon, tomatoes and stir-fry in 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add onions, garlic, coriander, pepper, oregano, vinegar, salt and tomato paste.
Stir-fry and add a bit of water, if necessary.
Add beans and stir 3 minutes. Add rice and keep stirring for an other few minutes.
Add hot water and let cook.
When rice is tender, add the remaining oil and cook gently for 5 minutes.
Serve with chicken or beef stew, Dominican style and avocado and tomato salad.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Tear dried beef into pieces and cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Wrap chicken with bacon and lay on top of the dried beef.
Salt and pepper to taste. Mix mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil and bake at 225° for 2 hours. Uncover and bake one more hour.

title: jello pinwheels
directions: Spray 8 or 9-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray on bottom and sides.
Wipe out excess with paper towel.
Mix Jell-O (any flavor) and water in 2-quart microwave bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Add miniature marshmallows and microwave 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until they are puffed and almost melted.
Stir until marshmallows are completely melted and mixture is smooth.
Pour into prepared pan. Refrigerate 45 minutes.
(Creamy layer will float to top.)
Roll Jell-O and cut into 1/2 inch slices.

title: 24-hour slaw
directions: Empty package of shredded cabbage and carrots into a large bowl. Add pepper and onions. In medium saucepan, combine sugar, oil, vinegar, celery seed, salt to taste and parsley flakes. Stir together over medium heat until sugar is dissolved. Pour hot dressing over cabbage. Cover and let stand overnight in the refrigerator. Yield: 8 servings.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in 8-inch square pan.
May be doubled and put in 9 x 13-inch, but use only 1 1/2 cups of sugar when doubled.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Mix stuffing direction from box with melted butter or margarine (reserve 1/3 dressing for the top).
Mix all ingredients together and put in greased casserole dish.
Cover with reserved dressing.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: angel food delight
directions: Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip, set aside.
Break up angel food cake in small pieces and mix with Cool Whip mixture.
Spread out in long cake pan.
Mix strawberries with strawberry glaze and spread over cake mixture. Chill.
(You can use fresh strawberries if you have them.)

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Beat eggs in small bowl. Add raisins and vanilla and mix. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: minted chocolate pears(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, water and vanilla in glass baking dish. Microwave, covered, on High for 5 minutes or until mixture boils. Peel and core pears; cut into halves.
Place in hot mixture. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Microwave on Medium for 5 minutes until pears are tender.
Cool.
Combine mint patties and cream in a small glass bowl; microwave on Medium for 2 minutes or until mints are melted.
Mix well.
Drain pears; place in serving dishes.
Top with chocolate mint sauce.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fresh vegetable soup
directions: Combine canned chicken stock, cream of chicken soup and 2 cups water; set aside.
Cook all other vegetables and chicken until very tender; cut in small pieces.
Puree all vegetables and chicken breast in blender.
Add pureed vegetables and chicken breast to stock.
Simmer on low flame 1/2 hour.
Serve with garlic crackers or corn muffins.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Place water in large bowl.
Add dry yeast and stir.
Add salt and sugar; stir.
Add 3 cups flour; stir.
Add egg and Crisco and stir well.
Add 3 cups flour; stir well.
Cover and refrigerate. When ready to bake, divide dough in half.
Knead half dough lightly.
Roll into about 8 x 16-inch piece.
Spread with half the oleo.
Fold dough lengthwise in pan.
Let rise to double in bulk. Brush other half of oleo on dough.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
May bake other half following day or use as follows.

title: marinade for swordfish
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over fish and marinate 30 minutes in refrigerator (if there is any leftover sauce from marinade, if you wish, boil it and use over the cooked swordfish).

title: ina's 11 day pickles
directions: Soak whole cucumbers in salt brine in crock (1 1/4 cups salt and cold water to cover). Let stand 3 days. On days 4 to 6, rinse daily with clear water. On the seventh day, cut in very thin slices and boil in a solution of 5 cups water, 3 tablespoons alum and 2 1/2 cups vinegar. Drain and cover with hot spiced vinegar made as follows: 3 pints vinegar and 7 pounds sugar and tie cinnamon and cloves in cheesecloth bag. Drop in solution. On days 8 to 10, reheat vinegar and pour over pickles. On eleventh day, seal in jars, covering with hot spiced vinegar. Makes 10 to 12 pints.

title: ginger snaps
directions: Cream:
1 cup sugar, 3/4 cups shortening.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix everything except rice and pork chops.
Reserve 1 cup of liquid mixture; mix rice with remainder.
Place in casserole with meat on top.
Cover with remaining cup of liquid.
Bake 1 hour covered at 350°.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: sweet and pungent carrots
directions: Heat oil; add carrots and stir 3 minutes. Add 1 cup water, sugar, vinegar and salt. Boil, covered, until carrots are tender. Blend and add cornstarch, 1/4 cup water and soy sauce and add to carrots. Stir and continue cooking 2 to 3 minutes until mixture thickens. Serve hot.

title: tender eye of round roast
directions: Combine tomato sauce, onion, water and beef bouillon; pour over roast in a deep casserole or baking dish.
Cover and bake 3 to 4 hours at 350°.
Turn roast over several times while it is baking.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Mix in small mixer bowl.
Spread on 12 English muffin halves. Quarter.
Broil about 5 minutes until browned.
If not wanting to use right away, freeze on flat pan.
Store in freezer bags.

title: pumpkin fritters
directions: Beat egg, sugar and salt until fluffy.
Blend in pumpkin. Sift together the dry ingredients.
Fold into egg mixture.
Add margarine and mix well.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls into greased frying pan.
Turn when golden, watching carefully. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Can be served with dinner or as a dessert.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Will keep in refrigerator a long time.

title: homemade mayo(boiled)
directions: Mix first 4 items until smooth.
Then mix next three items. Bring to full boil.
Stir constantly.
Cool and refrigerate.
Vary sugar and/or vinegar to suit taste.

title: overnight caramel french toast
directions: Combine sugar, butter and syrup in small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour syrup mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place 6 slices of bread on top of syrup.
Top with remaining 6 slices of bread.

title: creamy clam dip
directions: Gently stir together all ingredients and serve.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: tammy's meat balls
directions: If you use 2 pound ground meat, double your ingredients.

title: slovak potato soup
directions: Boil 10 medium potatoes (diced).
Cover with water to 1/2 of the pot.
Boil until soft.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add milk almost to top of pot.
Bring to a boil again.
Mix about 2 tablespoons flour with a little milk to make a paste.
Pour into potato mixture.
Bring to a boil to thicken it.
Add 1/2 pint sour cream and dill weed, cut up fine.
Heat through; don't boil.
Add 3 tablespoons vinegar.

title: ham delight
directions: Cut package of rolls into upper and lower half.
Put bottom half back into pan.
Mix margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion together.

title: mindie's tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna and cream of mushroom.
Boil noodles until tender. Mix noodles, tuna and soup together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until brown around the edges, approximately 20 minutes.

title: irish potato cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in layers.
Fill with marshmallow filling.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour and baking soda.
In another bowl, combine butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat.
Beat in egg.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in M&M's and nuts.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.

title: seafood wild rice salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder in a 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Add rice, pepper and shrimp; toss.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Spoon onto lettuce lined dish.
Garnish with cherry tomato halves and parsley.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Melt jello with water on low heat.
While jello cools, tear cake in small pieces.
Cut strawberries in fourths.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Put the tomatoes and onion in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Add margarine, sugar, salt and oregano.
Reduce heat to medium and cook for 5 minutes.
Add bread and stir.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart lightly greased casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: superb sausage dressing
directions: In large skillet, crumble sausage.
Cook sausage, onion and celery until sausage is no longer pink.
Stir in pecans; cook until sausage is lightly brown.
Pour mixture into large roasting pan to mix.
Add corn, mushrooms, butter, sage and fruit.
Stir well until blended.
Stir in eggs, then mix in the cornbread.
Add broth and stir to mix.
Beat the eggs and add to mixture.
Let set for 15 to 20 minutes to absorb the liquid.
If moister dressing is desired, add more broth.
Bake in same roasting pan or transfer to two 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until crusty brown on top.

title: chicken soup with homemade noodles
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender; shred. Put shredded chicken in pot with chicken broth and water; add celery, carrots and onion. Season with garlic salt and pepper.

Bring to a boil. Make noodles by adding egg, oil, milk, salt and pepper to flour. Mix until not sticky. Roll dough on floured surface to about 1/4 inch thick. Cut into strips. Add to chicken broth. Cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.

title: amish lemon pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour, salt and lemon juice, rind and milk.
Blend well.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and top with Cool Whip. Serves 8.

title: corncake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into bowl.
Mix together eggs, milk and oil.
Add, all at once, to dry ingredients and stir just to moisten.
Turn into greased 8-inch cake pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Or, cook in glass pan in microwave on 50% power for 3 minutes; turn for last 3 minutes (6 minutes total).

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Cook soup and milk on medium heat until smooth. Drain broccoli after cooking and put into 1-quart buttered casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture on top. Crumble 1/2 package Ritz crackers and put on top of soup. Dot crackers with 1/8 stick margarine. Bake until golden at 375°, about 45 minutes.
Put 1 can French fried onions on top about 5 minutes before taking out of oven.

title: cranberry orange salad
directions: Squeeze orange.
Pare apple.
Wash cranberries.
In food processor, mix apple, cranberries and nuts; add orange and pineapple.

title: ham loaf
directions: Have cured ham and fresh pork ground together.
In large bowl, to ground meat, add crackers and mix.
Add eggs and salt; mix.
Add milk until mixture will absorb no more.
Shape into loaf.
Put in roasting pan; pour water around loaf to about 1/2-inch.
Cover. Bake 3 hours at 325° to 350°.
Check about halfway through. May need to add water.

title: grandma lil's pineapple pudding cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool. Mix next 3 ingredients together.
After cake is cool, spread pineapple over the cake, then spread the cheese/pudding mixture evenly over the pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over next and scatter chopped nuts over all.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and oats; beat well. Sift flour, salt and soda.
Blend into first mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Dip in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add marshmallows.
Mix cherries, sugar, salad dressing and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Add nuts and coconut, if desired.
Chill and serve.

title: peach-marshmallow refrigerator pudding
directions: Soak gelatin in water.
Soften butter in top of double boiler. Add sugar, quartered marshmallows and egg yolks.
Take off stove; add gelatin.
Cool.
Add whipped cream and egg whites (beaten stiff).
Pour over peaches.
Line pan with vanilla wafer crumbs, saving a little for top of filling.
Let stand in refrigerator.

title: fruit cake
directions: Measure flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Sift all together.
Dice bananas, add to dry ingredients with oil, eggs, vanilla and pineapple with juice.
Stir to blend.
Do not beat. Bake in greased tube pan one hour and 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: large broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Mix everything.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle topping and dot with butter.
Bake at 350°.
Will serve at least 12 to 15.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat down in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix the next 3 ingredients and spread over cooled crust.
Mix the last 3 ingredients; let set until slightly thickened.
Pour over cream cheese mixture and refrigerate

title: cherry chocolate upside-down cake(microwave)
directions: Generously butter 12-cup ring cake dish; sprinkle with sugar to coat.
Spread half of pie filling in dish.
Mix remaining ingredients (including rest of filling).
Beat 3 minutes with mixer.
Pour into dish.
Cook at Medium 12 minutes, rotating every 3 minutes.
Increase power to High for 1 to 8 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched and begins to pull away from sides.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate. Let cool completely before slicing.
Makes one ring cake.

title: grandma jacobs' punch bowl cake
directions: Bake the cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

In bottom of punch bowl or very large bowl, break cake into larger than bite size chunks (use only 1/2 the cake at this point), then layer half of the pineapple and juice, half of the pudding, half of the bananas, 1 can of pie filling, half the nuts and half the coconut.
Spread with 1 carton of whipped topping.
Repeat the above.
Garnish with cherries, nuts and, if you want to be fancy, chocolate curls.
Serves 25.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Chop nuts in chopper until fine. Mix in batter.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan until brown. Cool in pan for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry goo
directions: Make sure egg whites are beaten.
Add other ingredients and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over graham crackers (crushed) or try corn flakes or Grape-Nuts or bran flakes; anything you want for crunchies.
Freeze for 24 hours.

title: german pizza
directions: In a 12-inch stove top or electric skillet over medium heat, brown beef with onion, green pepper, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper. Remove meat mixture from skillet and drain fat.
Reduce heat to low.
Melt butter.
Spread potatoes over butter and sprinkle with remaining salt.
Top with beef mixture.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Remove seeds and seams from peppers; boil 5 minutes.
Brown meat and onions.
Add rice and tomato juice.
Simmer until thick; season.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mile high buttermilk cake
directions: Sift together cake flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Add egg whites; beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour batter into three waxed paper-lined 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 more minutes or until cake tests done.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Spread Vanilla Filling between layers of cake.
Top with Orange Butter Frosting.

title: texas hash 2
directions: Brown hamburger with onion until onion is tender; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: roast pork with sauerkraut
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Rub roast with salt and pepper.
Put in large roasting pan; put in oven, turning to brown, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove roast; lower oven to 250°.
Scatter sauerkraut around roast.
In a bowl, mix the apples, onion, sugar, mustard and caraway seed.
Sprinkle this mixture over sauerkraut and drizzle wine over top.
(Can be refrigerated at this point and roasted later or next day.)
Cover and roast at 250° for about 4 hours, or until tender.
Moisten with more wine if it becomes dry.
Let rest 10 minutes before slicing.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in oleo.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: pasta with sun dried tomatoes and pine nuts
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add herbs.
Remove from heat.
Add sun dried tomatoes.
(Cut tomatoes in 1/8-inch slices.)
Toss lightly with cooked pasta.
Top with pine nuts.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: party mix with white chocolate
directions: Melt margarine and white chocolate in double boiler.
Mix dry ingredients in a big bowl.
Add melted white chocolate and mix until coated.
Spread on wax paper to harden.
Break into pieces.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken pieces on bottom of pan.
Cover with soup. Prepare box of Stove Top stuffing according to package directions. Layer over the soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in pineapple juice; add eggs.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Whip milk until stiff.
Add cooled Jell-O mixture; blend.
Pour into graham cracker crusts. Chill.

title: quick cherry salad
directions: Mix well.
Serve as is or frozen.

title: crab and cheese wontons
directions: Mix
crab
and cheese.
Put tablespoonfuls in middle of wonton wrappers.
Bring the 4 corners together and seal.
Fry in hot oil about 3-inches deep until light brown.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with marshmallows. Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour over marshmallows. Crush strawberries and mix with dry gelatin.
Pour this over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: rhubarb shortcake
directions: Mix together rhubarb, orange juice, sugar and honey.
Simmer about 10 minutes until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in strawberries.
Cover and chill.
To serve, spoon fruit mixture over shells and add topping.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on crackers.

title: ilse's onion pie
directions: Put onion and bacon in skillet and cook until glossy.
Remove from heat, add eggs, sour cream and stir.
Add salt and caraway seed to taste.

title: swiss steak
directions: Brown round steak in large skillet in small amount of fat. Drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer until tender (1 to 2 hours).
May need to add a little water and stir occasionally to keep from sticking.

title: aunt jeanette's rolls
directions: Combine hot milk, salt, sugar and shortening.
Let cool to room temperature.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to cooled mixture.
Add egg and flour.
Mix and set aside to rise 1 time, approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Shape and let rise 1 hour. Bake in a 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut when cool.
Should be golden brown.

title: best ever barbecue sauce
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, saute onion in oil over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Keeps up to 2 months in refrigerator.
Yields 2 1/4 cups.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves using high heat.
When syrup boils, blend in butter.
Stir frequently.
After it reaches a syrup stage (approximately 230°), reduce heat to medium when temperature reaches soft crack stage.
Add nuts.
Stir until temperature reaches hard crack stage, approximately 305°.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in baking soda.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour onto 2 cookie sheets with 4 sides.
Spread candy evenly over cookie sheets, loosen from pan as soon as possible and turn candy over.
Break into pieces when cooled.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook
squash and onion together until tender and cooked down. Mash
cooked
squash
and add sour cream, soup and salt and pepper.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and herb stuffing.

title: crumb cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix together, beating lightly after each addition, the butter, sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Pour into a prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with crumb mixture made by blending together the brown sugar, flour, butter, salt and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add hominy.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with crushed Fritos.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chips
directions: *Or 1 cup each chocolate chunks or chips and toasted nuts (pecans, walnuts, unsalted peanuts or Macadamias).

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In saucepan, combine gelatin, 1/2 cup of the sugar and salt. Beat together yolks, lemon juice and 2/3 cup water.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat and stir in peel. Chill; stir occasionally until partially set.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add remaining sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pile into cooled pastry shell.
Chill until firm.

title: tamale pie
directions: Crumble Fritos and cover bottom of casserole dish.
Chop onion; cook in small amount of oil.
Add ground beef.
Brown and drain.
Add other ingredients except cheese.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
When cool, add 2/3 cheese.
Pour in casserole dish.
Use remaining Fritos on top of meat mixture and remaining cheese on Fritos.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together and pour into loaf pan.
Bake 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecued beef ribs
directions: Dip ribs in flour and brown.
Remove browned ribs from pan. Add the ingredients to the pan.
Add ribs.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 220° or medium-low heat.
Turn once or twice.

title: ground meat and vegetables with bean paste over noodles
directions: Heat 5 tablespoons oil in preheated wok.
Stir-fry onion until fragrant.
Add ground meat; stir-fry until thoroughly cooked.
Add bean paste; stir-fry until fragrant.
Add water, cornstarch, sesame oil and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Cook until thickened.
Cook noodles by boiling water, adding noodles, bring to second boil and cooking over medium heat, about 4 minutes.
Drain noodles; place in bowls (individual).
Top with shredded vegetables and meat topping. Serve hot.
Mix well in bowls.
Serves 2.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk, cherry pie filling, pineapple and sliced bananas.
Mix them together and add nuts, if desired.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add red food coloring to make a pink color.
Chill about 1 hour before serving.

title: white bread
directions: Add yeast to warm water and sugar (1 teaspoon).
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix together the ingredients.
Marinate the chicken 2 hours or overnight.
Drain and broil 4 minutes (each side) or grill until done.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese.
Melt, then top with chopped onion and tomato.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together sugar, cocoa and flour in large bowl until no lumps remain.
Stir in melted butter.
Mix in eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Pour mixture into pie shell.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil carrots until just tender (8 to 9 minutes).
Layer onion, carrots and green pepper in a large bowl.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Cool slightly. Pour over vegetables.
Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 8 hours.
They will keep about 1 week.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan in a 350° to 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until done.

title: ham shanks and lima beans
directions: Pick, clean and wash
beans.
Put
in
Dutch oven large enough to hold
all
ingredients.	Place remaining ingredients in oven and let simmer for 4 hours, adding water as needed.

title: breakfast casserole - 4
directions: Tear bread into pieces and place in 9 x 9-inch baking dish or pan.
Brown sausages in a skillet and drain.
Place sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings; pour over sausage and cheese mixture.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cheese will rise to the top.
Best if made the night before and refrigerated until baking.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in casserole dish.
Add salt, pepper and pats of margarine on top.
Cover and microwave on High until potatoes are done.
Stir occasionally.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, and cornstarch well. Add milk, oleo, beaten eggs, and vanilla and mix well. Pour in pie shell and bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: green pea salad
directions: Combine peas, celery, lettuce and red onion in bowl. Mix juice from peas with mayonnaise and pour over pea mixture. Top with cheese and bacon bits.

title: fish fiesta
directions: If fish fillets are large, cut into 5 or 6 serving pieces. Arrange fish in ungreased square baking dish 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with onions and tomato slices. Sprinkle with lime juice, oil and parsley.
Cover and cook in oven at 375° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook until fish flakes easily with fork, about 15 minutes longer.
Garnish with lime wedges, if desired.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: one-bowl trifle chocolate oatmeal jumbles(makes 2 dozen cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Place spread in large microwavable bowl. Cover loosely with waxed paper. Microwave on HIGH (100%) for 30 seconds or until melted; cool slightly. Add remaining ingredients. Stir until well blended (dough will be very stiff). Drop dough by level 1/4 measuring cupfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets; flatten slightly. Bake 13 to 17 minutes just until set. (Do not overbake. Centers will be soft.) Let stand on cookie sheets 1 minute. Using wide spatula, transfer to wire racks. Cool completely.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and set aside.
Blend soup and cheese. Blend mayonnaise with milk and stir into soup.
Place broccoli in baking dish and cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Wash cucumbers and cut in sticks.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 4 to 5 hours.
Then drain and pack into six pint jars.

title: vanilla wafer pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add milk alternately with wafer crumbs, mixing well.
Stir in coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into prepared tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Yields 16 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven until lightly browned.

title: french onion soup
directions: Chop onions.
In large pan, melt butter and
cook onions until golden, but not brown.
Add enough flour to absorb butter, about 4 to 5 tablespoons.
Add chicken broth, 1 1/2 cans water and wine gradually while stirring well to avoid lumps.
Add more water or broth to taste and consistency; salt and pepper.
Simmer fifteen minutes until bubbly.
Pour in individual serving bowls.
Place a slice of fried or toasted crunchy French bread and sprinkle generously with grated Swiss cheese.
Broil until brown.
Serves 6.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into ball and roll in coconut.

title: velvet almond fudge cake
directions: Chop almonds and toast at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup on bottom of well-greased tube pan.
Set aside almonds and chocolate chips.
Measure remaining ingredients into mixing bowl. Blend.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips and almonds.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove and finish cooling on rack.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: grandma's lye soup
directions: Mix grease, lye and 1 quart water the night before and stir hard.
In the morning, add salt, 20 Mule Borax and 1 quart water. Boil 5 minutes, then leave on medium heat for 1 hour.
Set off the stove to cool.
Cut in any size cake desired and dry.
Age improves lye soup.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add flour, one cup at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Cut fruit in small pieces and mix with coconut and nuts.
Pour batter over fruit and nut mixture and mix well.
Bake in tube pan.
Start baking at 300° for 45 minutes. Then turn down temperature to 275° for 1 1/2 hours.
This cake can be frozen.

title: san francisco-style chicken
directions: Flour and pan-fry chicken breasts in a small amount of oil until brown. Drain and set aside. Cook rice as directed on package. Don't overcook.
Mix chicken soup with 1 soup can of water. Spoon rice into a 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay chicken breasts on rice. Add about half the soup on this layer, then put broccoli on fillets.
Add rest of soup and top with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: easy filled coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in Bisquick, egg and the tablespoon of sugar.
Mix well.
Turn dough onto surface, dusted with extra Bisquick and knead gently 20 times. Place in center of greased 15 1/2 x 12-inch baking sheet.
Roll out to 14 x 9-inch rectangle.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix well and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes in lightly greased pan/skillet, etc.

title: quick coffee ring
directions: Grease a large Bundt pan (cake pan).
Layer frozen rolls in pan. Mix cinnamon with sugar and pour over rolls.
Layer one at a time chopped nuts, brown sugar and pudding mix.
Slice margarine and place around the rolls.
Cover pan with cloth and set in warm draft free place overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Invert pan over serving dish and let stand a minute so syrup will cover cake.
Decorate with cherries on top if desired.
Best served while warm.

title: easy beefy crescent squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large frying pan, brown ground beef with onion, salt and pepper; drain.
Stir in sour cream.
Separate crescent dough into 2 large rectangles.
Place rectangles in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and 1/2 inch up sides to form crust.
Spoon hot mixture into crust.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, until deep, golden brown and crust is no longer doughy.
Refrigerate any leftovers. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix jello.
Fold in all ingredients and chill until firm.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, milk and margarine together.
Bake 3 layers at 350° until done.
Mix cream cheese, granulated sugar and powdered sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add 8 ounces Cool Whip. Grate frozen Hershey bars into frosting mixture.
Mix well and frost layers.

title: morgan's korean kal-bi ribs(from morgan's restaurant, bellevue, wa)
directions: Run all of the ingredients
in	blender for a minute or two. Combine flavors for 24
hours.
Marinate
to 5 pounds beef short ribs (or chicken pieces) at least overnight.	Grill meat or barbecue until
brown,
or	under broiler quickly.	(I use the crock-pot to cook meat, then brown on the grill.)

title: salad supreme
directions: Drain pineapple juice and add water to equal 2 cups of liquid. Then dissolve Jell-O by boiling and add the pineapple, cream cheese and marshmallows to melt.
Cool.
When cool, add the cream and put in a 13 x 15-inch pan and chill.

title: coconut pecan cake
directions: Combine oil, brown sugar and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Combine flour and the next 4 ingredients, beating well.
Gradually add buttermilk, a little at a time, then stir in vanilla, 1 cup coconut and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour batter into two greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: deep butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 2 eggs together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, eggs and vanilla together and spread over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: quick potato bake
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Slice the potatoes very thin. Place in a 2-quart casserole or a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Alternate layers of potatoes, grated cheese and soups, mixed with milk. Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish top with more grated cheese and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: sweet-sour spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in shallow pan.
Cook in slow oven, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Drain off fat.
Mix all other ingredients and cook until mixture thickens.
Cut ribs in small pieces.
Pour sauce over them and cook, covered, at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Mix well.
Layer tortillas, meat mixture and cheese in round casserole dish, ending with tortillas and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or for 5 minutes in microwave.
Serve with chopped tomato, shredded lettuce and sour cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: cream cheese dip for fruit
directions: Blend well.
Eat with apple slices, pears, strawberries, etc.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, eggs and sugar.
Mix in buttermilk, extract and vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box. Spread 2 cups of mix on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: ham vegetable chowder
directions: Heat water, broccoli, ham, carrots, celery, onion and salt to boiling in 4-quart Dutch oven.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Gradually stir milk into baking mix in small bowl (mixture will be lumpy).
Stir into ham mixture.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese.
Cover and let stand until cheese is partially melted (5 minutes).
Stir before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: karen's bread
directions: Thaw garlic bread.
Open the split halves and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While bread is baking, mix shredded Cheddar cheese, green onions, dill and mayonnaise (do not use Miracle Whip).
Mixture will be thick; you can add more mayo if desired.
Take bread from oven and spread mixture evenly on top of both sides (will be a nice thick layer).
Shake paprika on top. Place in broiler for approximately 3 to 5 minutes until nice and bubbly.
Watch it doesn't burn!
Cut into slices and enjoy!

title: chicken rice pilaf(djaj mah ruz m'falfal)
directions: Cook chicken in the water until tender.
Remove from liquid, debone and set aside.
Save the liquid.
Place almonds, pine nuts and butter in a saucepan.
Turn heat to low.
Stir, browning the nuts to a golden color.
Drain rice and add to the nuts.
Stir on low heat for 1 minute.
Add chicken pieces, broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil on high heat.
Lower heat, cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve on a platter with a sprinkle of cinnamon on top.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and molasses, mixing well.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, ginger and cloves.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
While still
hot, cut in half lengthwise and scoop out potato, leaving skins intact.
Mix potato with butter, sour cream, 1 1/2 cups of the cheese and onions.
If necessary, thin with more sour cream.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place mixture back in skins.
Top with remaining cheese and reheat until cheese melts.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and chill.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions, peppers and celery in olive oil until browned. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly over low heat for 1 hour or until liquid is reduced by half.

title: layered banana pudding
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the flour and brown sugar.
Stir in the milk; cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Remove from the heat. Gradually stir about 1 cup hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return all to the saucepan.
Bring to a gentle boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from the heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature, stirring occasionally.
Fold in the whipped cream.

title: chicken cheese casserole
directions: Boil chicken and take off bones.
Cook noodles in chicken broth. Add some water, if necessary.
Leave broth on noodles.
Do not drain.
Cream the margarine and flour.
Add milk and cheese (melt cheese in milk). Pour sauce over cut up chicken, noodles, onion and pepper.
Cook at 350° until bubbles in middle.
Will serve 20 people.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Stir the cornmeal into the boiling water with the salt and sugar. Stir 1 minute. Remove from fire. Add butter. Beat well and add eggs. Beat well. Add milk, beating again. Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch baking pan (Pyrex). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Melt butter.
Combine butter and milk to the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into dish and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: grannie's muffins
directions: Preheat oven at 400°.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Add rest of ingredients.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Fill 12 muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: light summer casserole
directions: Brown meat in salt (no oil or shortening).
Drain on paper towel.
Spray casserole with Pam.
Layer zucchini slices (unpeeled), 1/2 of meat, onion slices, tomato chunks and croutons. Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: applesauce coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease
13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cake mix (save marbling pieces),
applesauce,
water, oil and eggs together.
Pour 1 1/2 cups	of
batter into smaller bowl; add marbling
package and beat.
Pour
yellow batter into pan. Put mounds of chocolate mixture on
top and marble.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake
at 350° for 33 to 38 minutes.
Cool completely.	Serve with
Cool Whip or applesauce.

title: lemon angel food cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix, pie filling and lemon juice and beat well. Pour in a jelly roll pan.
Do not spray pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When cool, frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pepper steak
directions: Season meat and coat sides with flour.
Brown in oil.
Add liquid from tomatoes plus 1 3/4 cups water to it.
Add cut-up onions and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Cut green peppers into strips and add to meat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add whole tomatoes to gravy and simmer 15 minutes more. No extra seasoning is needed for gravy.
Serve over rice.

title: very ritzy chicken(great company dish)
directions: Dip chicken breasts into beaten eggs; coat with bread crumbs. Heat oil in a frying pan on medium heat.
Add coated chicken and brown lightly on both sides.
Remove from pan and place in a baking dish, topping each breast with a slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Mix together remaining ingredients in a saucepan and cook until mixture gets hot and thickens.
Pour over chicken and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve over angel hair pasta.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ham.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly on one side of each ham slice.
Roll up and secure with wooden pick.
Cover and chill.
Carefully slice each roll into 1/2-inch pieces.
Serve with toothpicks.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: cheese-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash mushrooms.
Remove stems and mince finely.
Mix egg yolk with cream cheese.
Add onion and minced stems.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 10 minutes.
(May be made ahead of time.)

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix and pour all ingredients into pie shell.
Bake 5 minutes at 425 degrees.
Reduce heat to 325 degrees and bake until pie doesn't shake.

title: christmas jelly roll
directions: Mix batter as directed on box of cake mix.
Pour batter into 2 jelly roll pans (11 x 15-inch) and bake for 15 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Invert on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar. Roll up and let cool.
After cooling, unroll and spread sherbet on cakes (about 1 pint per cake, either use all one flavor or half of each).
Don't spread too thick to roll.
Roll up, wrap in foil and freeze.
Slice just before serving.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix the margarine, flour and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar together (first 3 ingredients).
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan-butterscotch coffee cake
directions: The night before, partially defrost dough.
Place nuts evenly in bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Place rolls on top of nuts. Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls, mixed with cinnamon.
Combine margarine and brown sugar and heat to a simmer.
Pour over dough. Let rise overnight.
Bake in preheated oven at 375°
for 30 minutes.
Turn upside down on serving dish.
Let cool.

title: aunt vollie pound cake
directions: Put all together and beat for 12 minutes.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: jello pie
directions: Put one large and 1 small jello in bowl and 2 cups of steaming hot water.
Add strawberries.
Let it jell and put on top of mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until well blended.
Add melted butter; mix well.
Put in refrigerator and chill.
Roll in balls.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in double boiler; dip balls into chocolate mixture with toothpick.
Put on waxed paper or buttered pan.
Keep balls in a cool place.

title: jello delight
directions: Layer crushed pretzels in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar and butter over pretzels and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Blend cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Layer over pretzels and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Dissolve Jell-O in water, then add strawberries.
Layer onto Cool Whip and cream cheese, then refrigerate.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Heat sour cream.
Add sugar, melted margarine and salt and stir to dissolve.
Cool to lukewarm.
In a large warm bowl, add 1/2 cup warm water and sprinkle yeast into water.
When dissolved, add sour cream mixture, then eggs and stir in flour.
Put batter in refrigerator overnight.
Divide into 4 parts.
Roll each section into round circle on floured surface.
Cut into pie shaped wedges.
Roll into crescent rolls.
Put on greased baking sheet and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken. Melt 1/3 cup oleo and add 2 tablespoons liquid smoke. Dip chicken pieces in this (coating well). Place chicken in casserole dish and bake at 320° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground chuck in medium skillet over medium heat until browned.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Wipe skillet with paper towel.
Return meat to skillet and stir in tomatoes, water, garlic and Italian herb seasonings.
Cover and bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions omitting salt and fat.
Drain well and set aside.
Cook spinach according to package directions omitting salt and fat. Drain well and squeeze excess moisture from spinach.
Combine spinach and next 4 ingredients.
Stir until well combined.
Set aside.
Place half of cooked noodles in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Top each half each of cottage cheese mixture and American cheese.
Spread half of meat mixture. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Melt chocolate and butter (I use microwave).
Combine powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour hot chocolate mixture over and beat until spreading consistency.
If more liquid is needed, use a few drops of hot water.
Makes enough frosting for 10 x 14-inch pan or 2 layers.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix up whatever amount you need and pour the dressing over according to your own taste.

title: sidewalk chalk
directions: Combine paint and water in a container.
Slowly stir in the plaster of Paris.
Pour into waxed paper cups, plastic cups (grease with vegetable oil) or candle molds.
Remove chalk when hard (about 3 hours), then allow it to dry for 4 days.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked and drained broccoli in baking dish.
Mix in chestnuts.
Add cheese to top of mixture.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons melted butter over mixture.
Mix crumbs with remaining butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana coconut cake
directions: Mix together and bake in Bundt pan for 38 to 40 minutes.

title: easter eggs
directions: Mix sugar, butter and cream cheese together.
Add your choice of listed fruits.
Shape into eggs.
Let dry for a while.
Dip into dipping chocolate or roll in chopped nuts.

title: delicious apple cobbler
directions: To form dough, mix together flour, Crisco and milk.
Spread out on floured surface and roll out.
Sprinkle dough with sliced apples, cinnamon to taste and apple pie spice.
Roll dough with apples inside to form a jelly roll effect.
Slice up dough and lay sideways in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easter ham pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and let stand.
Make dough by combining flour, 2 eggs and water.
Roll out and place in a 9-inch pie pan.
Fill with ham mixture and top with crust.
Beat 1 egg and brush on top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cover chicken in water that just barely covers the chicken. Add onion, salt, pepper, garlic, oregano, green pepper, Italian seasoning and parsley flakes.
Cook until chicken is tender (save broth).

title: northern michigan salad
directions: Use as many of the ingredients as desired for the salad.
Mix as you would any other salad.

title: spiced iced coffee
directions: Add spices to coffee.
Boil 5 minutes; strain.
Add sugar and chill.
Serve in glasses, containing little cracked ice and top with cream.
Dust with additional cinnamon.

title: mrs. law's chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and Crisco, then add sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Then add all dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325° in 10-inch tube pan.

title: tomato salad
directions: A large platter works better than a bowl.
This way you can display each ingredient and the presentation is excellent.
Remove core of lettuce and break in 3-inch pieces and place on bottom of platter.

title: white christmas fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil over moderate heat 9 to 10 minutes to 238°, soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat and allow to stand until lukewarm (110°), about an hour.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture just begins to lose its gloss and hold its shape. Quickly stir in walnuts and turn into oiled pan.
Let stand until firm before cutting.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello as directed (1/4 cup less water).
Add sugar and cool.
Then add apples, bananas and pineapple.
Let set up in refrigerator.
Boil 1/2 cup pineapple juice, 1/4 cup sugar, flour and beaten egg, stirring all the time.
Let mixture get cold. Prepare Dream Whip; fold into cold mixture and spread over jello. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: artichoke puffs
directions: Cut artichokes and swiss cheese into fourths.
Combine mayo and parmesan cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Place one piece artichoke on bread.
Spread mixture over artichoke and top with swiss cheese.
Put under broiler until hot and cheese melts.

title: slow ball dip
directions: Cut a round circle in the bread and hollow out. Set aside. In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Stir in the clams, clam juice, onion, beer, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, red hot sauce, salt and pepper until well blended.
With 2 sheets of aluminum foil large enough to cover loaf, fill loaf with cream cheese mixture and seal tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: yule delights
directions: Cream margarine and cheese together, then add other ingredients and mix well.
Roll into long rolls and refrigerate several hours.
Slice into thin rounds and place on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until edges brown.
May be frozen and baked later.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix eggs and oil.
Combine buttermilk and soda.
Add this to eggs and oil.
Stir in flour, cornmeal and salt.
Add corn, onion, peppers and cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven until done.

title: herbed pasta-tuna bake
directions: In greased 2-quart baking dish toss shells, tuna and celery. In blender mix mayonnaise, milk, parsley and green onions until smooth.
Pour over tuna mixture; toss to coat.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Chop cranberries, apples (cored and peeled) and oranges (peeled) in food processor.
Prepare jello according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients; let set.
(Will take about 18 hours to jell.)

title: vickie's lettuce salad
directions: In a large bowl,
break
up
lettuce,
cauliflower
and bacon. In a small bowl, mix the mayonnaise, cheese and sugar. Add the dressing to the lettuce mixture and mix well.

title: hidden valley oyster crackers
directions: Combine oil with Hidden Valley dressing mix and other spices. Pour over crackers.
Stir well.
Heat, in warm oven, 15 to 20 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Cool on paper towels.
Store in Tupperware.

title: thai cucumber salad
directions: Put
cucumbers, onions and chili peppers in salad bowl. Stir together
ingredients
and pour over vegetables in bowl. Store in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix pumpkin, eggs, oil and water. Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, pumpkin spice, soda, salt, nuts, nutmeg and cinnamon. Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients slowly.
Mix well.
Place into greased and floured loaf pans (2).
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on box.
After cake is cool, tear cake into pieces, then layer all ingredients in a large bowl and top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: corn souffle
directions: Grease large glass bowl or casserole dish. In large bowl mix all ingredients.
Do not drain whole kernel corn.
Use the water in can. Pour mixture into glass bowl or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, until golden brown on top, uncovered.
Very good.
Very easy.

title: dependable divinity
directions: Mix water and sugar.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Place marshmallow cream in bowl and pour hot syrup into cream.
Beat until the mixture loses its gloss.
Add nuts, vanilla and salt. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: beefy-tortilla pie
directions: Coat bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate with vegetable cooking spray and line with tortillas.
Set aside.
Cook ground chuck in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Combine meat, chilies, onion and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon mixture into prepared dish.

title: chocolate chip ice cream pie
directions: Coat bottom and sides of an 8-inch pie plate lightly with butter.

title: quickie 8 can soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly.

title: quick chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In large pan (Dutch oven pot), mix all the can contents together along with chicken and spices.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
When it's good and hot, turn off burner and add chips, standing them up all over the pot.
Do not stir.
Then sprinkle cheese on top.
You can put in oven 15 to 20 minutes at 375°, but this is optional.

title: white bread
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar together.
Add shortening, flour and salt.
Mix well for about 5 minutes, if using a mixer or knead by hand for 5 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions, and peppers very fine. Then add sugar, salt, and vinegar.
Add spices tied in a cheesecloth bag.
Cook slowly uncovered for 2 hours until thick. Remove spice bag.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add egg yolk, then gradually add milk and stir.
Add lemon flavoring and coconut.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir slowly while cooking.
Pour in baked pie crust and add meringue.
Sprinkle with coconut and brown in oven.

title: sour cream and dill chicken
directions: Place chicken in single layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine soup, soup mix, sour cream, lemon juice, dill and mushrooms; pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red cabbage with apples(160 calories)
directions: In a large skillet over medium-heat in hot oil, toss sliced cabbage until well coated and slightly wilted.
Add apple, wine, sugar, salt and pepper.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes, tossing occasionally until tender-crisp.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package and place in greased casserole.
Mix onion, celery, cheese and mayonnaise and spread over vegetables.
Melt butter, then put in crumbled crackers; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: classic jalapeno dip
directions: In food processor, mince artichoke hearts, also jalapeno peppers.
Combine all ingredients in ovenproof bowl; mix, then smooth top of mixture.
Bake, uncovered, until edges are brown at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with blue corn chips.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add coloring, cocoa and vanilla.
Beat well; add sifted flour, salt and baking powder.
Alternate flour mixture with buttermilk.
Put soda in vinegar and sprinkle over batter; fold in until well blended (don't beat).
Bake in three 8 inch pans at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour over crackers, stirring to mix. Place on baking sheet and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken divan casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to directions. Thoroughly combine all ingredients together and put into 2 pans that are 12 x 20 x 2-inches. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes about 50 servings.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each one.
Mix flour, salt, and baking powder together.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add coloring with milk.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs
in
milk.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Pour in a pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a deep dish baking dish.
Put blackberries in a saucepan with 1/2 cup sugar.
Heat until hot.
Combine 1 cup sugar, Bisquick and milk.
Pour in baking dish
over melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Add blackberries.
Do not stir.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: whiskey pralines
directions: Cook sugar and milk over medium heat for approximately 10 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add butter, whiskey and pecans.
Whip until mixture hardens.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls into hot oil until brown.
Turn over and brown on other side.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over them and serve.

title: cheese and potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion and water in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
In heavy skillet, melt butter; add flour.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir mixture slowly into potatoes; cook and stir until thick.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: black bean and pasta soup
directions: Heat oil in 4-quart pot.
Add onion and garlic. Stir until onion softens.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add pasta.
Reduce heat to low. Simmer, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes until pasta is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar.
If desired, garnish with pepper strips.
Good accompanied with corn bread.

title: green rice
directions: Pour boiling water over rice and let set for 3 minutes. Combine all ingredients well and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° (or until sides are brown and top begins to brown).

title: milky snacks
directions: Put bananas, eggs, and honey in a blender and blend until smooth.
Add orange juice, milk and cinnamon and blend again. Pour into tall glasses and serve.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute onion, celery and pepper.
Mix all together. Put cheese on top.
Put jalapeno to taste.
Put in hot oven until cheese melts.

title: chewy peanut butter strips
directions: Mix ingredients and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into strips.

title: brown sugar icing
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Boil to soft ball stage (236°); pour slowly, beating constantly, onto egg whites.
Add flavoring. Continue beating until icing holds its shape when dropped from spoon.

title: lamb and potato korma
directions: Wash and remove excess fat from meat, set aside.
In a pressure cooker or pot add oil and warm over medium-high heat. Add cardamom, cloves, cinnamon, and zeera.
When it sputters, add the meat, onion, ginger/garlic, cayenne, salt, and turmeric. Brown the meat.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes in pressure cooker or 1 hour in a regular pot.
The meat should not be fully done at this point.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Combine coconut and margarine. Reserving 2 tablespoons coconut mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom and up side to rim of 9-inch pie plate; chill. In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon, fruit cocktail, almonds and cherries; mix well. Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into prepared crust. Garnish with reserved coconut and additional fruit if desired. Chill 4 hours or until set.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef
and saute with onions.
Add both sauces and mix well.
Boil noodles until done.
Drain and rinse well.

title: venison chili
