directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain and add rest of ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes in the skillet or cook in crock-pot for 1 hour.

title: turkey spaghetti
directions: Mix and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to soft ball stage (238° to 240°).
Remove from heat and stir until mixture cools and thickens.
Spoon out on buttered wax paper, aluminum foil or parchment paper.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Cover; refrigerate for 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls. Place about 3 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten in a crisscross pattern with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: oriental surprise salad
directions: Combine first
ingredients
in
large
bowl and toss well. Cover and
refrigerate at least 30 minutes. Add cashews and noodles; toss again.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: oyster stew
directions: Combine milk, cream, salt and pepper in a large heavy kettle. Heat over medium heat until milk is scalded.

title: ashley's crispy chocolate bars
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch morsels with peanut butter in large saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add corn flakes and stir until well coated.
Spread mixture into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Let stand at room temperature about 10 minutes, then cut into bars.

title: ezy bars
directions: Put melted butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs, chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss apple pie
directions: Mix egg, sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Add chopped apples and walnuts.
Place in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook syrup, butter and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir well.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Put in 2 baking pans and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts and remove from bone.
Place in casserole dish and pour mushrooms over chicken.
Mix cream of chicken soup with sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Melt margarine and mix with Ritz crackers and poppy seed.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until knife blade comes out clean.
Ovens vary so you may want to lessen the heat.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Sprinkle ribs with garlic salt.
Make sauce with remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Bake in deep pan at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Mix together all ingredients in large bowl.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole baking dish.

title: split pea soup(with rye croutons)
directions: In a dutch oven or large pot, heat oil over medium heat.
Add carrots, onion, potato, sweet potato and garlic.
Cook, stirring until softened, about 3 minutes.
Add broth and split peas.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, partially covered, until vegetables are tender and peas have broken down, about 40 minutes. Season with pepper.
Meanwhile, in a small skillet, cook bacon until crisp, 3 to 5 minutes.
Transfer to a plate lined with a paper towel.
Ladle soup into bowls and garnish with bacon and croutons.

title: green peas and onions
directions: Slice large ripe tomatoes in 1/2-inch rounds or wedges and place in a large, flat pan or dish one layer deep.
Sprinkle generously with salt, coarsely ground pepper and crumbled oregano. Carefully pour oil so that tomatoes are just covered.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Allow at least 1 hour to marinate.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low heat setting for 4 to 6 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Boil chicken for 30 minutes.
Dice chicken.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour soup over chicken.
Top with prepared stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ooie gooie bars
directions: Slice one pack of cookies and flatten in 9 x 11-inch glass dish.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Spread over cookie dough.
Layer second roll sliced cookies on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together.
Add vanilla, then peanuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper lined cookie sheets. Chill.

title: chicken - stuffing casserole
directions: Fix stuffing according to directions.
Mix milk, soup and chicken.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Place 1/2 stuffing in bottom of pan.
Pour soup and chicken over stuffing and place remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Separate egg yolks and whites.
Put egg whites in separate bowl; beat well for several minutes.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup sugar. Mix the Eagle Brand, lemon juice, 3 tablespoons sugar and egg yolks well; pour into pie crust.
Pour meringue over pie mixture. Bake at 350° until meringue is brown.
Chill and serve.

title: haystack eggs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter 8 or 9-inch glass pie plate or round baking dish.
Spread shoestring potatoes evenly over bottom of pan. Makes 4 indentations into potatoes, down to bottom of dish, each about 1 1/2-inches across.
Carefully break 1 egg into each indentation.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 10 minutes; add cheese and parsley.
Return to oven and bake until cheese melts and eggs are set.
Cut into 4 wedges and serve immediately.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add egg yolks, beating thoroughly.
Add milk, gradually, while mixing.
Cook mixture in a double boiler until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat until smooth.
Mash the bananas; add to sugar and butter.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add gradually to banana mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Fold in well beaten eggs.
Pour into an 8 or 9 x 4 x 2-inch greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cheesy enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add seasoning, water and beans; mix well.
May need to add a little more water.
Fry tortillas a few seconds on each side in hot oil.
Divide meat mixture on tortillas and roll up.
Place, seam down, in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 2 cans soup; spread over enchiladas.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese 1
directions: Cook macaroni by directions on box and drain.
Add margarine to cooked macaroni.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour egg and milk mixture over cooked macaroni.
Sprinkle grated cheese over macaroni and stir it into the egg and milk mixture, saving some to sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until mixture is firm.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Mix all ingredients into large kettle and cook until tender. Season with oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper.

title: impossible french apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie pan.
Mix apples and spices; turn into pan.
Beat remaining ingredients, except Streusel, until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with Streusel.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Slowly add the crumbled cream cheese to the sugar and mayonnaise.
Add crushed pineapple and the cherries.
Whip heavy cream and fold into the mixture.
Freeze in trays or in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: lasagne(authentic italian recipe)
directions: Chop onion, garlic and parsley fine; fry slightly in hot oil. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, bay leaf, salt, pepper and water; stir until well mixed.
Toss in hamburger and sausage.
Break up meat with fork in little pieces.
Now cover the tomato sauce and cook on low for 45 minutes, stir occasionally.

title: seafood lasagne
directions: Peel off the shells from the shrimp, starting at head end so tail can be nipped off easily.
Make a shallow cut along the back of each shrimp and remove the dark intestinal vein.
If the shrimp are large, cut them lengthwise in half.
If necessary, remove and discard the tough muscle at the side of each scallop.
Rinse scallops with cold water; drain and pat dry with paper towels. Cut large scallops crosswise in half.
Rinse the sole fillets with cold water and pat dry with paper towels.
Cut (slicing across fillets) into several pieces.
Refrigerate until ready to use. Peel the shallots and separate into sections if necessary.
Slice horizontally toward the root, leaving the slices attached at the root.
Slice vertically, again leaving the root end uncut, then cut across the shallot to make fine dice.
Heat butter in a medium saucepan.
Add the chopped shallots and saute, stirring, until soft but not brown, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add the shrimp and scallops and season with salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until shrimp turn pink and scallops become opaque, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the white wine and bring just to a boil.
Remove the pan from the heat.
Lift out shrimp and scallops and reserve them.
Set the cooking liquid aside.

title: one pan supper
directions: Fry in shortening or bacon grease until potatoes start to brown.
Cut up into thin slices a Polish sausage.
Add to ingredients in pan.
Cover and let cook until potatoes are golden brown.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Defrost the bread dough until soft enough to pull off and roll into small balls.
Arrange approximately 48 small balls in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.

title: sweet cherry soda
directions: In a blender container, combine cherry sauce and ice cream. Cover and process until smooth.
Pour half of mixture into each of 2 tall glasses.
Fill glasses with club soda.
Garnish each serving with a whole cherry.

title: swiss corn chowder
directions: Add potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper to boiling water.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
Make a white sauce with margarine, flour and milk.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Add corn and undrained vegetables.
Heat; do not boil.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: diet pickles
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers into slices about 1/4-inch thick.
Mix cucumbers and salt.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, drain and press out all the juice possible. Rinse once in cold water. Combine vinegar, sugar substitute and spices. Boil 1 minute. Add cucumbers and simmer 5 minutes.
Pack cucumbers into clean, hot sterile jars to within 1-inch of top. Fill jars with hot liquid to top.
Seal tightly.
Makes about 12 pints.
Cucumber Slices:
46 calories per pint.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine ingredients together first, then fold in 9 ounces Cool Whip. Put in graham cracker crust.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oats and let stand.
Cream white and brown sugars and oil.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture.
Add flour, cinnamon and salt into oats; beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Don't use mixer.
Sprinkle coconut on top of cake before baking.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sour cream and sugar until light and fluffy. Sift plain flour and baking soda together.
Add flour to mixture alternating with the eggs.
Add flavor and bake in Bundt or tube cake pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, parsley, onion flakes and dill in a bowl.
Cut dried beef into small pieces and fold into mixture. Cut rye bread into chunks.
Dip the bread!

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs.
Press crumb mixture into 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes. Layer coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, and nuts. Pour condensed milk evenly over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch squares.
Cool.

title: sour cream and chive mayonnaise
directions: Combine egg, salt and vinegar in bowl of food processor, fitted with steel blade. Pulse just to blend.
With processor running, very slowly add the oil until the mixture emulsifies (or thickens). Add sour cream and chives.
Pulse again just to blend.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage together and drain well.
Add garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Melt in Velveeta cheese. Spoon mixture onto slices of party rye bread.
Broil for a few minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead gently for 30 seconds.
Roll out dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Use biscuit cutter to cut out rolls.
Place rolls into lightly greased pan.
Bake at 400°
for about 20 minutes.
May also be cooked in muffin pan or floured and spooned into pan.

title: barley with monterey jack one dish dinner
directions: In a large saucepan, cook barley in 3 tablespoons butter, stirring for 2 minutes.
Add 4 cups water and salt.
Bring liquid to boil and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Let cool.
Mix tomatoes, half and half, scallions, olives, mushrooms and chili peppers, 3/4 of the cheese, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Combine well and transfer to a baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: clam dip
directions: Mash cheese.
Add well drained clams.
Moisten with clam juice to proper consistency.
Add lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce. For color, add chopped parsley.
Serve cold with crackers or potato chips.

title: quick-haluski with cabbage and low-fat cottage cheese
directions: Chop cabbage; boil until tender.
Boil shells as per directions on box and drain.
Melt oleo; drain cabbage and add to oleo.
Combine shells
with cabbage, then add 1 carton of low-fat cottage cheese.
May be topped with dry or chopped fresh dill.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a quick boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool syrup.
Mix fruit and juice into syrup and freeze at least 3 hours.
Before serving, remove from freezer and thaw to slushy consistency.
(This can be made several days ahead of serving and frozen, but can take up to 8 hours to thaw.)

title: fluffy fruit dressing
directions: Blend marshmallow cream and orange juice with rotary beater. Stir in salad dressing and vanilla.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
For fruit salads.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans on bottom of pan.
Make cake mix according to package.
Pour over coconut and pecans.

title: spicy tea mix
directions: Mix together.
Store in tight container.
For 1 serving, place 1 well rounded teaspoonful in a cup of boiling water.
For 1 quart, dissolve 1/3 cup mix in 1 quart of boiling water.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Place chicken and broccoli in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over chicken and broccoli.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vermont maple pecan pie
directions: Melt oleo and blend in flour until stiff mixture.
Beat eggs and white sugar until fluffy.
Add oleo-flour mixture and beat again.
Blend in white Karo and maple syrup and water.
Add to egg mixture along with chopped pecans.
Save a few half pecans to garnish top of pie.
Bake in uncooked pie shell about 1 hour at 350°.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add flour, salt and pepper to the yeast, sugar, oil and warm water.
Mix well.
Knead 5 minutes.
Let rise 30 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: In top of double boiler, melt morsels over boiling water. Stir in sweetened condensed milk. Remove from heat. Stir in cereal and peanuts. Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper lined baking sheets. Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Store at room temperature in loosely covered container.
Makes about 2 pounds or 48 candies.

title: colorful punch
directions: Mix liquids together.
When ready to serve, add sherbet. Serves 50.

title: wine cookies
directions: Blend sugar, wine and oil well.
Add flour gradually, stirring until a wet, but not sticky, dough is formed.
Take small pieces and form into rings.
Dip one side into sugar.
Bake, sugar side up, on cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: heath candy cake
directions: Bake German chocolate cake according to directions on box in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Poke holes in cake using the handle of a wooden spoon.
Make lots of holes, but don't overlap.
While cake is still warm, pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Then pour caramel topping over cake.
Let set in the refrigerator to cool.
Crush 3 Heath bars; sprinkle over top.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 3 more crushed Heath bars over Cool Whip.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup and milk.
Place in baking dish and form a loaf.
Mix soup and 1/2 can milk.
Pour over meat loaf and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Is very good with potatoes placed around meat and some of the soup mixture poured over them also.

title: nutty oatmeal-chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Process oats in a blender or food processor until ground.
Beat butter and sugars at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until blended.	Combine ground oats, flour and next 3 ingredients.
Add to butter mixture, beating until blended.
Stir in chocolate and pecans.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7-8 minutes or until golden brown; remove to wire racks to cool. Yield:
6 dozen.

title: lemonade pies
directions: Stir lemonade and milk in large bowl until well blended.
Add food coloring to suit your taste.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip until well blended.
Pour into graham cracker pie crusts.
Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: chocolate chip applesauce cake
directions: Mix well flour, sugar, soda, cocoa, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, cloves and salt.
Add shortening, applesauce, eggs, 1/2 cup nuts, 1/2 cup chocolate chips and raisins.
Beat until smooth; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on top brown sugar, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit pizza(makes 2 pizzas)
directions: Bake cookie dough 8 to 10 minutes. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Spread on cookie dough while still warm. Add fresh fruit.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add sugar.
(Let set for 1 hour.)
Add marshmallows to Cool Whip.
(Let set for 1 hour.)
Drain pineapple.
Mix all together.
Put in glass bowl.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread the 2 packages of crescent rolls on a large baking sheet to make crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip, horseradish and pepper.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with vegetables and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Keeps well.
It can be made a day ahead of time. (Doesn't take many veggies.)

title: never fail rolls
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, salt and hot water with electric mixer.
When this mixture has cooled to lukewarm, add yeast which has been dissolved in 1 cup lukewarm water.
Add eggs, mix well. Sift flour slowly into mixture, beat well.
Cover, place in refrigerator until chilled.
Shape into rolls and let rise in warm place for 2 hours.
Bake in 400° oven until brown.
Brush with butter if desired.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: stay-in-bed stew
directions: Combine in crock-pot. Cook all day on low or in oven at 250° for 5 hours.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Butter bread and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Top with bacon (can substitute sausage or a vegetable) and cheese. Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour into dish.
Cover and let set in refrigerator overnight.
In the morning, mix cornflakes and melted butter.
Pour on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: fresh apple muffins
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar and margarine; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour with milk and vanilla to creamed mixture, beating well.

title: cherry sauce for ham
directions: Drain cherries.
Combine juice, wine and cornstarch.
Add lemon juice, salt and allspice.
Cook and stir until clear and slightly thickened.
Add butter and cherries.
Serve warm with baked ham.

title: queen anne cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, then flour and baking powder.
Have cookie sheets greased and floured lightly.
Spread the mixture very thin with spatula. Sprinkle with chopped nuts (pecans, peanuts or almonds), then with sugar.
Bake in a moderate oven at about 400° until a delicate brown.
Cut into squares; remove from baking sheet immediately. Makes about 80 (2-inch) cookies.
Store in airtight tins.

title: todd's favorite pancakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Combine egg, milk and salad oil. Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Bake on hot griddle.
Makes about 12 dollar size or 8 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, butter and 2 tablespoons of sugar; put in baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup of sugar with mixer.
Stir in Cool Whip. Spread on top of pretzels.
Mix jello, water and strawberries and let partially jell, then pour over Cool Whip mixture and let chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: my mother's cornstarch pudding
directions: Line sides and bottom of serving bowl with sponge cake.
Warm milk.
In a small mixing bowl, mix together the cornstarch, sugar, egg and vanilla; mix until creamy.
Pour into warm milk; stir to boiling.
Pour over prepared layer; sprinkle shredded dark baking chocolate on top.
Allow to cool at room temperature, then put in refrigerator.

title: texas company eggs sunday rest meal
directions: Whip eggs and milk.
Scramble until they just hold their shape, soft and a little runny.
Spread eggs in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
While hot, spread with sour cream.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until done.
Peel and cool.
Cut lengthwise.
Put in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients until melted.
Pour over potatoes.
Cook at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add eggs and cream.
Stir to mix (dough should be lumpy and soft).
Drop from tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes. Makes 12 large biscuits.

title: chicken broccoli alfredo
directions: Slice chicken into chunks and fry in tbsp of butter with garlic pepper seasoning salt and cook thoroughly. Set aside with 3 cups cooked broccoli well strained, cook 1 pound of your favorite pasta. * Sauce = melt one stick butter on medium heat, then add cream cheese and melt. With wire whisk slowly stir in milk and then add parmesan cheese and pepper. Heat till well blended then combine chicken, broccoli, pasta and sauce. Yummy!

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook over medium heat for about 30 minutes or until beets are softened.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix everything together. Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Blend in the remaining ingredients.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef bourguignonne
directions: In large fry pan,
brown meat in butter.
Add mushrooms and onion; continue
browning
until
tender.
Add
remaining ingredients except wine.
Simmer,
stirring
frequently, until sauce thickens.
Add red wine; continue simmering for 15 to 20 minutes until meat is
tender.
Serve over buttered noodles or rice.

title: shirley's open candied yams
directions: Parboil yams and then peel.
Cut in thick slices.
Place in baking dish.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Cover yams with mixture. Dot with margarine.
Put lemon juice over yams.
Pour water in. Cut 1/2 orange in slices.
Place on yams.
Other 1/2 of orange squeeze over yams.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until yams are tender.
Syrup is thick, baste after.
Yields 6 servings. Eat with love from the kitchen of Shirley Murden.

title: blueberry-cream cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla well.
Whip cream.
Fold cream into cheese mixture and pour into pie shell.
Spread blueberry filling over top and chill.

title: easy lemon meringue pie
directions: In saucepan, combine pie filling mix and sugar. Gradually blend in lemon juice and water until smooth. Stir in egg yolks. Bring to a full boil over medium heat. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add lemon peel and pour into baked pie shell. Top with Meringue, sealing well at edges.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool 2 hours before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Blend flour, sugar, soda and salt. Add to mixture oil, eggs and buttermilk and mix well. Add raisin bran. Cover tightly. Bake as needed at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: big soft ginger cookies
directions: Combine flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl beat margarine with an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds to soften.
Gradually add the 1 cup sugar, beat until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses; beat well. Stir dry ingredients into beaten mixture.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls (1 heaping tablespoonful dough each).
Roll in the 2 tablespoons sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 1/2 inches apart.
Bake in a 350° oven abut 10 minutes or until light brown and still puffed (do not overcook).
Let stand for 2 minutes before transferring to rack to cool.
Makes 24 (3-inch) cookies.

title: punch
directions: Mix water and sugar together in a large pan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved; set aside to cool.
In a large container, mix pineapple, orange and lemon juices; add cooled sugar water mixture to Jell-O (dry); mix well.
Add bananas (that have been mashed thoroughly); mix well and freeze until ready to use.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Combine first four ingredients in mixing bowl.
Heat last three ingredients to 110° to 115°, warm to touch.
Pour liquid mixture over flour mixture.
Blend at low speed for one minute. By hand, stir in 1 cup additional whole wheat flour and 4 to 4 1/2 cups all-purpose flour.
Knead on floured surface about 5 minutes. Place dough in greased bowls; cover and let rise 45 to 60 minutes until doubled in bulk.
Punch down dough; divide in half.
Shape each half into a loaf shape.
Place in two 9 x 5-inch greased loaf tins.
Cover loaves; let rise 30 to 45 minutes until light and double in size.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes until loaf sounds hollow when tapped.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Slice when cool.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix in heavy pan and stir with wooden spoon.
When this begins to boil fast, time for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and Marshmallow Fluff.
Stir until chocolate and marshmallow are blended.
Add walnuts.
Pour into a 14 x 9-inch pan. Spray pan with Pam before emptying the fudge into pan to set.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and drop by spoonful onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
You may brush with melted butter while still warm.
Yields
8 to 10 biscuits.

title: flounder with lemon butter sauce
directions: Season flounder fillets with garlic salt and white pepper. Coat fillets with flounder and then beaten egg.
Next, fry fillets in skillet, using vegetable oil.
Cook fillets for about 3 minutes on each side.
Place flounder fillets on a serving plate.
In the same skillet, add butter, lemon juice, salt, pepper and garlic. Mix until blended and pour on top of fillets.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add everything else except nuts and mix. Add nuts in with mixture. Pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Use either red or green peppers.
Remove seeds from peppers; blend peppers in blender.
Use vinegar for liquid.
Mix in sugar; bring to rolling boil and add Certo.
Bring to full boil again, stirring constantly for 4 minutes.
Skim off foam.
Pour into jelly jars.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick spray.
Dip chicken in margarine, then coat with remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, or until tender.

title: quick hoppin' john with cabbage
directions: In a large, heavy bottom pot, fry ham, onion and green pepper in canola oil over medium high heat for 5 minutes.
Add cabbage, chicken broth, red pepper flakes, bay leaf and parsley.
Stir. Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Drain and rinse black-eyed peas.
Add peas to pot; stir and simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix dry pudding and cream in bowl with spoon.
Chill until thick.
Beat on high until it looks like whipped cream.

title: chocolate milkshakes
directions: In covered blender container at high speed, blend all ingredients until smooth.
Pour mixture into chilled 12 ounce glasses.
Serve milkshakes with large straws.

title: no-bake cake
directions: Cut cake into 1-inch cubes.
Prepare pudding with milk.
Place cake and marshmallows in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour prepared pudding over top, completely covering cake. Chill at least 1 hour. Cover top with Cool Whip.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients as listed and mix well in large Tupperware container with cover.
Refrigerate.
May have to be stirred down. Take out by spoonful, roll in flour and shape biscuits.
Bake in moderate to hot oven until golden brown.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine eggs, flour, milk and salt in bowl.
Mix just until moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 12 popovers.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Combine with electric mixer; chill. Dip apples, bananas, strawberries, etc.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Pat in bottom of pan.

title: celery relish
directions: Soak first 3 items in salt water overnight.
Drain well.
Add chopped celery and remaining ingredients.
Mix well; bring to full boil and can hot.

title: butter sauce
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Mix sugar and flour; add to margarine.
Add milk; cook until thick like a gravy.
Remove from stove.
Add vanilla.
Spoon some over your favorite piece of cake.

title: grandma dooley's jam cake
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, allspice and cloves. In a separate bowl, add soda to buttermilk. In a third bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Add jam and mix well. Add milk and flour mixtures alternately to creamed mixture, blending well after each addition. Stir in nuts. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Add 1
cup coconut to cake mix.
Mix and bake according to directions	using
a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
While cake is hot, punch
holes in cake.
Combine Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut.
Pour
over
cake.
Frost when cool.
Combine Cool Whip, pecans and coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown chops
on
both
sides in small amount of cooking oil; drain off any fat.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chops. Simmer
minutes
or until fork-tender.
Serve with white rice or noodles.

title: fresh apple pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer. Spread on muffin halves. Quick freeze. Remove and cut in quarters. Freeze in plastic bags until ready to use. Broil for 5 minutes or until just browned and bubbly.

title: cranberry-orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot
water;
add
cranberry
and beat until smooth.
Add orange
juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add celery and apple.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan or mold. Half a recipe would fill an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cheesy onion bake with toasted rounds
directions: Grate the cheese and mix with the onion, mayonnaise and cracked red pepper.
Bake in a covered baking dish in a 225° to 250° oven for about 25 minutes.
Using an electric knife, thinly slice the French breads into rounds.
Lay the slices on a cookie sheet and lightly brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with coarse ground black pepper and bake 20 to 25 minutes in 300° oven.
Serve the hot cheesy onion bake as a dip with the toasted rounds.

title: grilled potatoes in foil
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasonings in large bowl until well blended.
Stir in potatoes and onions to coat.
Divide potat mixture evenly among six 12-inch square pieces of heavy-duty foil. Seal each to form packet.
Place foil packets on grill over medium-hot coals (coals will have slight glow).
Grill, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: polish hamburgers
directions: Mix hamburger, pork, eggs, chopped onion, green pepper and milk together.
Add bread crumbs to form a patty.
Brown patties in a little oil until browned on both sides.
Remove patties.
Add water to juice and thicken with flour water to make gravy.
Put patties back in gravy and let simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sheath cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour; set aside.
Mix margarine, shortening, cocoa and water in a saucepan and bring to a rapid boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and stir well.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into a greased 16 x 11-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Make into little nest or just put into bottom of greased baking dish.
Dice onions and tomatoes.
Set aside.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, stir together oat bran, flour, baking soda and salt.
In a separate large bowl, cream the butter or margarine with sugar and vanilla extract. Beat in egg whites. Gradually add oat bran mixture and mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop from a level tablespoon onto cookie sheets sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Stir in milk and whole container Cool Whip.
Put in pie crust.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours.
Top with crushed peanuts or grated chocolate.

title: coconut-orange chess pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, mixing well.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture, stirring well.
Add coconut.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until filling sets.
Yield: One 9-inch pie.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Cook meal, sugar, salt, shortening and milk in a saucepan until thick (like cereal).
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast that has been dissolved in warm water.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour to form soft dough.
Knead.
Cover and let rise.
Punch down.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with butter.
Let rise. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: fudgesicles
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs and corn syrup.
Stirring constantly, mix a little hot milk into cocoa mixture.
Gradually add more milk until all milk is used, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth, thickened and coats the spoon. Pour into molds, ice cube tray, paper cups, etc., and freeze until stiff.
Add sticks.
Freeze thoroughly.

title: microwave rhubarb pudding
directions: Combine rhubarb, water and sugar in a 2-quart microwavable bowl; cook, uncovered, 8 minutes.
Add pudding mix.
Cook 1 minute.
Serve warm.

title: paradise cove cheesecake
directions: Blend cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk until creamy.
Add lemon juice and blend into mixture.
Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate at least an hour.
Serve.

title: brown 'n serve rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, shortening and 2 1/2 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour to form soft dough.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes. Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: In a large skillet, brown pork in fat.
Add 1/4 cup water; cover and simmer until tender (about 1 hour).
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Add cornstarch mixture, pineapple, green pepper and onion rings to skillet.
Cook (continue stirring) over medium heat until mixture thickens. Cover and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve over cooked rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: gary's creole cabbage
directions: In large pot, brown meat, pepper and onion; drain.
Add chopped cabbage, Ro-Tel and tomatoes.
Add cheese soup.
Cook about 2 hours on slow heat or simmer.
Good served with cornbread.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; set aside.
Add cream of chicken soup to stuffing mix and mix.
Add 1 to 2 soup cans of water (mixture should be slightly soupy).
Add squash.
Place in greased baking dish; dot with margarine.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown and firm to touch.

title: chocolate lush cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well. Put into an 8 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 300° or until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix together and press into a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: easy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs with sugar and butter. Press on bottom of 9-inch pan.

title: sand cups
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix together.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes or until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip. Gradually stir in 1 cup of crushed wafers.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Top with remaining crushed wafers.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
This will make 8 servings.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add the egg, milk and flour and baking powder mixture.
Add the berries.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Eat while warm with butter.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel
and
slice eggplant 1/4 inch thick; sprinkle with salt and
let stand 15 minutes.
Blot off moisture with paper towel. Fry
eggplant in olive oil until lightly brown or soft to
touch. Saute
ground beef with onion and garlic; salt and pepper slightly.
Add
tomato
sauce
and
cook
for about 30 minutes. Layer
eggplant, then beef mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Use 8 x 10-inch casserole to layer eggplant. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown chili meat and drain.
Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: double pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in square pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar in pan.
Arrange pineapple and cherries over sugar mixture.
Mix cake as directed on label.
Pour batter in pan. Bake for 50 minutes.
Turn upside-down on cake plate.

title: mom's guacamole
directions: Peel avocados and break into chunks; do not smash.
Add sour cream, lemon juice, garlic and salt.
Mix well, but don't smash the avocados.
Strain a jar of salsa to remove liquid.
Add strained salsa to avocados and mix.
Serve with warm corn tortillas or tortilla chips.

title: fried corn
directions: In
a 10-inch Dutch oven heat margarine until sizzling. Add corn, sugar, salt and water.
Fry for 6 minutes.

title: asparagus parmigiana
directions: Cook asparagus until just barely tender; drain. Add butter. Arrange in shallow buttered baking dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Over this pour egg and milk blended together.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and oregano. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle lightly with more cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: tequila sour
directions: Blend with ice in blender.
Pour into cocktail glasses. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Put butter and marshmallows together in a pan over low heat until melted.
Stir in popped corn and beat well.
Press into a tube cake pan and let cool.

title: baked seafood salad
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients, then add the next ingredients except for the butter.
Stir into seafood mixture.
Spoon into a 6 x 10 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine 1 cup breadcrumbs with melted butter.
Sprinkle over seafood mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cabbage gumbo
directions: In a large pot, saute onion and pepper in oil for one to two minutes; add tomatoes, okra and cabbage.
Stir well.
Add water; and on high heat, bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium, cover pot and cook 30 to 45 minutes.
Add salt to taste.
Stir occasionally. Great with corn bread.

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cook sugar, syrup and water to hard ball temperature.
(Will form a ball when dropped in glass of cold water and "clink" when tapped against side.)
Beat into the egg whites, pouring in very slowly.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts. Beat until stiff.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Thirty minutes before roast beef is done, prepare Yorkshire Pudding.
Heat square 9 x 9-inch pan in oven.
Heat 1/2 cup vegetable oil in pan over stove.
Mix flour, salt, milk and eggs. Mix all ingredients with hand beater just until smooth.
Take out heated pan from oven; pour in 1/2 cup heated oil and add the mixture.
Put in 425° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
When golden brown remove from oven and immediately cut into squares and remove from pan.
Usually there is still oil in the pan.
If you wait to remove the Yorkshire Pudding from the pan the excess oil will be absorbed into the pudding and will stick to the pan.
Serve with butter.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; salt and pepper to taste.
Cut cabbage coarsely.
Chop onion.
In a 3-quart casserole dish, add 1/3 of the cabbage, 1/2 of the hamburger meat and 1/2 of the onion. Layer these.
Add 1/3 of the cabbage and the last 1/2 of the hamburger meat and the last 1/2 of the onion and the remaining 1/3 of the cabbage.
Pour tomato soup over the top.
Do not stir or mix.
Cover and bake in 350°
oven for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: mushroom scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, 1/2 cup cheese, onion, salt and milk.
Add potatoes and mix well; put in greased baking dish.
Top with 1/4 cup cheese and bake at 350° until potatoes are tender, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: super nachos(easy layer meal)
directions: Cook ground meat in a skillet; drain.
In an oblong baking dish, spread refried beans on bottom; spread the meat on top of beans.
Spread Old El Paso salsa over meat; sprinkle cheese.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Spread the sour cream over top and garnish with black olives.
Serve as a meal with tortillas or as a dip with nacho chips.

title: mother's lemon apples
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
Bring to rolling boil all ingredients except apples.
Add the apples, stirring carefully to cover with liquid.
Cook on medium to medium-high until apples are transparent.
Remove apples with slotted spoon, leaving juice to continue cooking until slightly thickened.
Pour over apples and allow to cool before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Arrange bread slices in greased baking dish. Cover bread with browned, drained sausage.
Mix together beaten eggs, mustard and milk.
Pour over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cover with undiluted soup.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook together until veggies are cooked; add chicken.
Cook this in a 5-quart stew pan.
Eat with cornbread.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger and onion.
Mix in other ingredients. Bake 1 1/2 hours or put in crockpot and cook on high for 2-3 hours.

title: craver dip
directions: Blend catsup gradually into cream cheese.
Add salad dressing, onion, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco; blend thoroughly.
Fold in shrimp; chill at least 1 hour.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: chicken saute
directions: Fry chicken in butter until white on the outside.
Take chicken out and saute broccoli and cauliflower in remaining butter.
When thawed, mix in broccoli cheese soup and milk.
Heat until simmering, then pour chicken back in and cook for about 10 minutes.

title: brew
directions: Stir juices, water and sugar together in pitcher until sugar is dissolved.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Pour over cracked ice which has been placed in glasses.
Serves 4 cups.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Then mix together flour, soda, sugar and cocoa.
Add to liquid mixture.
Bake in 2 layers in a 350° oven until done.

title: walcie's hamburger soup
directions: In large stewer, brown hamburger; drain.
Add water.
Bring to a boil.
Add all ingredients.
Stir well, until mustard is dissolved.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cream chicken with parsley
directions: *Individual pieces (i.e. breasts, thighs) may be used.

title: light tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions omitting salt and oil in the water.
Drain and combine with the tuna, mayonnaise, celery, onion, bell pepper and peas.
Set aside.

title: *whole wheat rolls
directions: In a large bowl, pour in scalded milk.
Add salt, shortening, 5 tablespoons sugar and beaten eggs.
In a small bowl, combine 1 tablespoon sugar and yeast with the warm water.
Let yeast mixture set for at least 10 minutes and then blend with the ingredients in a large bowl.
Add 1 1/2 cups whole wheat and 1 1/2 cups white flour.
Blend this mixture to a soft dough.
Continue to gradually add the rest of the flours, remembering to keep the dough soft. Keeping the dough soft is the real secret to making light rolls.

title: dietetic "3 minute delite" poppy seed cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add liquids and mix until smooth.
Add 1 can poppy seed filling and/or 1 cup of chopped nuts (optional). Beat well on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Use a 10-inch tube pan. Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until tested done.
Cool cake before removing from pan.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in 1 stick of margarine; add to other ingredients. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
(Dot with butter before baking.) (This tastes better if it is made in a long dish so it will be thin.)

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter and add sugar.
Mix and add nuts.
Cook until mixture reaches 290°.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Pour on cold board (I used cookie sheet).
Spread.
Place 2 Hershey bars on top and then spread chocolate as it melts.
Let cool completely.
Crack up.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix 1/2 cup bread crumbs, 1/2 cup milk, 1 egg and 4 tablespoons ketchup together.
Make into balls in pan.

title: jane's baked rice
directions: Mix all together in a 1 1/2 quart casserole. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Stir once during baking.

title: spinach noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a slow cooker.
Cover and cook 4 to 6 hours on low heat.
Serves 8.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and spices, then mix with remaining ingredients.
Toss and serve.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: In 3-quart pan, heat oleo.
Cook onions until tender.
Stir in flour.
Slowly stir in water.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients (except lemon slices).
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Add more water, if needed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in shallow baking dish.
Cover with apple slices.
Pour apple juice on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take off cover and bake 15 more minutes.
Serve and enjoy!

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Hollow out a round loaf of bread (preferably rye or pumpernickel).
Save the pieces of bread removed and use them for dipping.
You can use crackers or cut up vegetables.

title: zucchini cake(just like apple pie)
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar and melted margarine; set aside. Cook the zucchini with lemon juice until tender.
Add the sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; cook 1 more minute, then add 1/2 cup of the flour mixture that was set aside.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Take 1/2 of the flour mixture; pat down into pan.
Put zucchini mixture on top.
Top with remaining flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Enjoy!
Tastes like apple pie.

title: shrink-ups
directions: Cut shapes out of the lids (often you can get them from meat department of grocery stores).
Color and draw on the plastic. Place them on a cookie sheet and bake them at 350° for a few minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
While cooling, mix vanilla pudding as directed, adding cream cheese.
Layer strawberries on cake.
It is best to slice strawberries.
Next, pour pudding and ice with strawberries.
Serves 12.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a casserole dish in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned navy bean soup
directions: Wash beans and place in a large kettle. Cover with the 2 quarts of cold water.

Simmer for 3 minutes and then allow to soak for 1 hour. Add ham, salt, pepper, bay leaves, carrot and celery. Cover and simmer for 3 1/2 hours. Add onion during the last 1/2 hour. Mash beans slightly. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir in mayonnaise; salt and pepper to taste.

title: meat loaf recipe
directions: Mix ingredients well. Shape into loaf. Prepare sauce to pour over before baking.

title: party mix
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, place first 3 ingredients and microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir well.
Add cereals, pretzels and nuts, mixing to coat.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes, until evenly toasted.
Yield: 2 1/2 quarts.

title: one bowl pecan pie
directions: Mix all in one bowl.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into Jell-O in large bowl until completely dissolved. Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened. Stir in whipped topping until smooth. Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut. Spoon into mold. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Makes 10 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake
in
a greased, floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix together.
Marinate 20 minutes to 2 hours.
Great on chicken, pork or shrimp.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Put flour and sugar in large bowl.
In pan bring to boil butter, shortening, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour and sugar; mix well.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, cinnamon and soda.
Mix well and pour batter into greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple plus juice and pie pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over and pour melted oleo over that. Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chinese meatballs
directions: Make small meatballs with hamburger, onion, bread crumbs, salt, egg, tomato sauce and garlic powder.
Shape into balls.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Work shortening with a spoon until fluffy and creamy.
Add sugar gradually, while continuing to work with a spoon until light.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with the bananas, a small amount at a time, beating smooth with a spoon after each addition.
Turn into a greased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: curried herring with dill(this recipe sounds odd, but it's consistently a hit!)
directions: Combine all ingredients except herring and mix well.
Add the herring and refrigerate until it is time to serve.
Great with pumpernickel bread.
Serves 25 to 30 people as hors d'oeuvres. Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: potato casserole
directions: Sprinkle cubed cheese and onion over potatoes.
Place pimento, garlic salt and parsley on top.
Put bread cubes over top of casserole.
Pour margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate icing for cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Cook to a boil, stirring constantly. When it foams up, reduce heat, then cook down again. Add a big spoon of butter and 1 spoon vanilla. Beat well and spread on cake. Cooking time is about 15 minutes; will be soupy.

title: simplified oat bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients with wet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Serves 1 dozen.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Beat 8 eggs and milk with seasonings. Pour over croutons and cheese.
Fry and drain meat and crumble over casserole.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake covered 350 for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: homemade bread or rolls
directions: Mix well and
let
rise 1 hour and work down.
Let rise another hour and
work
out
into
either 6 loaves of bread or about 6 dozen
rolls.
Bake
at 350° for 1/2 hour for rolls or 45 minutes for bread.	Grease top after baking with lard.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Drop by 1/3 to 1/2 cupfuls or by ice cream scoops.
Bake at 350° for approximately 12 minutes.
Makes a bunch!

title: bacon-cauliflower salad
directions: Prepare the night before serving.
Use large bowl that can be covered tightly.
Break lettuce and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Dice onion.
Layer in this order: lettuce, onion, bacon and cauliflower.
Combine the remaining ingredients and spread on top.
Cover tightly.
Mix well just before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread rice in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken on top and add 1/2 envelope dry onion soup on top.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours. (May increase temperature and cook for shorter time.)

title: orange-glazed scallopini with rosemary
directions: On wax paper, mix flour, 1/2 teaspoon of the salt, half of the pepper and half of the rosemary.
Coat chicken in flour mixture; shake off excess.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; saute 5 minutes or until just cooked, turning once.
Place on platter.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and put half of crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Mix in sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
In separate bowl, mix together pudding mixture and vanilla.
Fold cream cheese mixture into pudding.
Pour into pan on top of crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top. Refrigerate to set.

title: fruit fritter batter
directions: For apple fritters, add 4 tablespoons of sugar, 1 1/2 cup pared chopped apples and 1/4 teaspoon of cinnamon.

title: pork chops crock-pot
directions: Dredge pork chops in mixture of flour, salt, dry mustard and garlic powder.
Brown in oil in large skillet.
Place browned pork chops in crock-pot.
Add can of soup.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours (high for 3 1/2 hours).

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 40 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until not quite done.
Mix mushroom soup with 1/2 cup milk and add onion juice.
Place layer of broccoli in casserole dish, layer of bread crumbs, layer of mushroom soup mixture and layer of cheese.
Repeat, making 2 layers.
Top with buttered crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican croissant
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray glass pan, 9 x 13-inch or 2-quart.
Spread crescent rolls across bottom and sides of pan. Brown hamburger and 1/2 an onion in pan.
Drain.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: pork chops with dried cherries
directions: Sprinkle chops lightly with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook pork chops on high heat 4 to 5 minutes each side. Transfer to plate.
Cover.
Keep warm.
Add shallots and thyme to skillet.
Cook 1 minute.
Add Port wine, chicken broth and cherries to skillet.
Bring to boil.
Cook until reduced by half, about 3 minutes.
Return pork chops to skillet.
Cook until meat is heated through.
Sprinkle with parsley when serving.

title: "easy" cucumber pickles
directions: Cut ends off cucumbers and pack in a gallon big-mouth jar. Cover with vinegar and let set for 6 weeks.

title: party treats pecans
directions: Beat egg white until stiff, then mix the rest of ingredients and dip pecan halves and put on buttered foil. Bake at 275° until light brown about 20 minutes.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Drain crab meat.
Chop eggs. Blend all ingredients. Serve as stuffing for tomato on lettuce leaf.
Top with slices of avocado and sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 8 or 9.

title: german honey cookies(makes 100 to 125 cookies)
directions: Heat sugar, Crisco, honey and molasses in pan until shortening is melted.
Cook over low to medium heat and stir to prevent scorching or crystallizing.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil. Separate graham crackers and lay side by side. Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter, margarine, and sugar; cook for 2 minutes. Add pecans and pour over crackers. Bake 10 minutes. Let cool about 3 minutes; remove from cookie sheet. Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: golden broccoli soup
directions: In 8-cup measure, place the broccoli, carrot, onion and water. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 5 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.

title: banana chips
directions: Slice bananas very thin. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake in oven on cookie sheet at 350° until crisp.

title: greek summer vegetable salad
directions: Place the tomatoes, onions, bell peppers, and cucumbers on a serving platter.
In a bowl, whisk together the olive oil and vinegar.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour the vinaigrette over the vegetables.
Crumble the feta over the salad, sprinkle the olives and oregano over the top, and serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into cakes.
Fry in shortening (or oil) until done, browning on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.

title: hot sausage casserole
directions: Cut vegetables in 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in large skillet and saute.
Brown sausage.
Put vegetables and sausage in casserole. Add juice, paste, garlic, salt, sugar, oregano and allspice.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream pecan coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; fold in vanilla and sour cream and mix gently.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans. Spoon half the pecan mixture into a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Cover with half the batter.
Spoon on remaining pecan mixture and cover with batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden skewer inserted in center comes out clean. Do not overbake.
Set aside for 10 minutes.
Run sharp knife around edge.
Invert onto plate.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.
Yield:
12 to 15 servings.

title: macaroni cheese bake
directions: Melt margarine and add flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Do not brown.
Stir in milk, salt and pepper.
Cook until smooth and thickened.
Combine drained macaroni with white sauce.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Place under broiler for a few minutes if a browner crust is desired.
Serves 8.

title: rice cooker sausage jambalaya
directions: Brown smoked sausage in skillet.
Place all ingredients together in an electric rice cooker.
Cook just as you would cook rice.
When the bell rings on rice cooker the jambalaya is ready. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: grape salad
directions: In a 9 x 5-inch dish, dissolve the raspberry Jell-O in the hot water; add the grape juice.
Add the pineapple and chopped pecans. Chill until set.
Combine the cream cheese and Cool Whip and spread over Jell-O mixture.
Sprinkle nuts over top and chill.

title: sweet graham snacks
directions: Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with graham crackers.
In a saucepan, bring butter and sugar to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from the heat. Stir in nuts. Spoon over the graham crackers. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan onto foil. Cool. Break apart. Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: sorghum pudding cake
directions: Mix separately from cake.
Pour this mixture over unbaked cake mix.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Knead 5 minutes.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Add sauce, cheese, etc.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until crust is brown on bottom.
Makes 1 crust.

title: apple bread puddings
directions: Toast bread.
Break into cubes and turn into 8 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch ovenware dish.
Add hot milk.
Let stand 15 minutes. Beat together eggs, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and sweetener until light.
Add apples and raisins into bread mixture. Place into shallow baking pan.
Fill with water.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes clean, 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm or cold.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: Saute in butter; onion, garlic, celery, parsley and bell pepper.
Add shrimp and cook 10 minutes.
Combine cheeses, half and half and flour.

title: shells and tuna
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; rinse and drain.
Add tuna, eggs, pepper and celery to suit your taste.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix and sprinkle chopped tomato on top for garnish.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet until light in color.
Remove from pan, leaving all sausage drippings.
(With fork, tear up sausage and reserve.)
To drippings, blend in flour, salt and pepper (to taste).
To this add milk slowly, stirring.
When mixture begins to thicken, add sausage.
Delicious over homemade baked biscuits or crunchy buttered toast.

title: chicken chow mein casserole
directions: Cook chicken; save broth.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve over fluffy rice.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large baking pan and bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: vanilla custard
directions: In a large bowl, slightly beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually. Slowly add scalded milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour into slightly greased custard cups.
Place cups in pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 minutes.
Test with knife.
When knife comes out clean, custard is done.
Cool, then refrigerate.

title: wimpy's(linda baker's sloppy joe recipe)
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, pepper and rest of ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes; serve on rolls.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Soak
pickles
in
cold water a couple of hours.
Put a head or	two
of dill and several onion slices in jars.	Split each pickle
or	slice
and fill jars.
Put alum the size of a pea
in each
quart jar, also 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring syrup (vinegar, water,
sugar) to a boil and pour over pickles hot. Seal.
Put jars
into canner.	Cover with water.
Bring water to a
boil. Turn
off heat.
Let cool in water.
Pickles will shrink, but will fill out in a couple of weeks.
Will be good to eat in 2 weeks.

title: green beans
directions: Bring to boil all ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger rice
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet; drain fat.
Stir in water, catsup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover.
Let stand until cheese melts.

title: meat loaf #2
directions: Soak bread in water; squeeze out excess moisture. Combine bread, meat, egg, seasonings, onion and 1/2 can tomato sauce. Mix well. Shape into a loaf in a shallow baking dish. Combine remaining tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and water. Pour sauce over meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: old-time buttermilk fudge
directions: Put soda in
buttermilk
and let stand 3 minutes.
Cook all ingredients,
including
buttermilk,
to
soft ball stage. Cool and beat
until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan or plate. Cut into squares
when set.	Nuts, coconut or other flavorings may be added.

title: kahlua number 1
directions: Simmer water, sugar and coffee gently, uncovered, for 1 hour. Add vanilla and vodka.

title: fast fixin' fish
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter; stir in soup mix and parsley blended with water.
Add fish.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until fish flakes.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer casserole dish with chicken, chips and cheese.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel in saucepan; heat to boiling.
Pour half over layer.
Make another layer of chicken, chips and cheese.
Pour remaining soup mixture on top.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese is melted and bubbling hot.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco together.
To butter and Crisco, add sugar until creamed.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well. Alternately, add flour, milk and water.
Beat well.
Pour in floured and greased tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes longer.
Put pan in cold oven; set temperature and do not open door while baking.

title: uncooked lye soap
directions: Pour water into small enamel, stone or glass containers. Dissolve the lye in the water, stirring gently with wooden spoon until dissolved.
Mix in a well ventilated room, but not in a breeze.
Let the lye water cool until the container feels cool to the hand.
Melt the fat in an enamel pan and stir with a wooden spoon.
Cool the fat until the spoon begins to leave a track in the mixture.
Pour the lye solution into the fat in a small steady stream, stirring until the mixture is honey-like in texture. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into molds or boxes that have been lined with wax paper.
Cover the soap and let stand 24 hours.
Cut into bars.
Place soap in open air, but avoid drafts and cold.
Let cure for several weeks before using.
Makes about 9 pounds.

title: herb sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients and form into small balls.
Bake on a rack in a shallow pan for 20 minutes.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: In skillet brown meat; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn, green pepper and tomato sauce.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. In a separate bowl, prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions except add 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spoon corn muffin mixture around outer edge of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top corn bread with cheese and remaining onions; bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: southern smokies
directions: Brown sausage 5 to 10 minutes.
While browning sausage, mix in crock-pot on high setting, jelly and barbecue sauce.
Drain sausage, then mix in crock-pot.
Simmer at least 30 minutes, then serve.

title: mccartney fudge
directions: In a large bowl, mix semi-sweet chocolate chips, chopped nuts, marshmallow, margarine and vanilla.
In a 3-quart saucepan, mix sugar and milk.
Cook over medium high heat; stir constantly. When mixture boils, continue cooking 6 minutes.
Stir constantly. Pour ingredients in bowl; stir until chips dissolve and mixture is smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Let set 6 hours or overnight.
Refrigerates well.
Let stand at room temperature for easy cutting.

title: easy no-cook fudge
directions: Cream the cream cheese until soft and smooth.
Slowly blend in sugar; add melted chocolate and other ingredients.
Press into well-buttered shallow pan; refrigerate until firm.
For softer fudge, blend in 1 teaspoon milk.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and soup.
Place on bottom of casserole dish, then drain green beans and put over meat mixture.
Add mashed potatoes, then top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Add chopped onion, celery and carrot. Cook 2 minutes.
Add cauliflower; cover.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add broth and bring to boil 5 minutes.

title: split pea and potato soup
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, melt the margarine.
Add the onion and cook, uncovered, until soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir in the beef broth and water and bring to a boil, about 4 minutes.
Add peas and potatoes.
Adjust heat so that the mixture bubbles gently, cover and cook for 30 minutes, or until the peas and potatoes are tender. Remove from heat and cool 10 minutes.
In an electric blender or food processor puree the soup in 5 batches, whirling each batch about 15 seconds.
Return to the pan, set over low heat and bring to serving temperature, stirring often.
Add pepper.
Serves 4.

title: deluxe cheese cake
directions: Mix all together, beat at high speed for 2 minutes. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: special cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Mix together Zwieback crackers, butter and sugar. Line bottom of cheese cake pan (9 1/2 x 3-inch).

title: linguine with shrimp scampi and broccoli
directions: Melt 1/2 butter in oil and saute shrimp for 2 minutes.
Put aside.
Put 1/2 butter, 2 cloves garlic and olive oil in.
Add broccoli, wine, parsley and pepper.
Mix together, then add shrimp.
Serve over cooked linguine.

title: sole casserole
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Lay fish in serving size pieces on bottom of pan.
Pour shrimp soup over fish (undiluted). Crumb the croutons and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening and mix with sugar, add eggs one at a time. Add flour, nuts and chocolate chips.
Batter will be sticky! Spread in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool before cutting.
(These don't cut too neatly!)

title: squash casserole
directions: Over low heat, saute squash and onions until tender-crisp. Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in shrimp soup and water chestnuts.
Place in greased casserole and sprinkle with buttered crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cut the pork chops off the bone in small pieces.
Put in pot and fry.
Get the link sausage, slice thin.
Put aside until the pork is done, then fry the sausage.
Get out of pot and drain most of the grease, leave enough to fry the onion (cut up in small pieces), green onion (cut in small pieces) and bell pepper (cut in small pieces).
When that is done, add the meat and fry a few minutes more, then add the rice and fry about 10 minutes all together; then add spice, salt and pepper.
Add water and cook until it is done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar, and chopped pecans by hand.
Let stand 1 hour.
Mix flour baking soda, cinnamon, and salt until well blended.
Add oil and eggs.
Bake in a greased and floured bundt pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Combine the boiled potatoes, celery and red onion; set aside. Separately combine the last 3 ingredients and add to potatoes; toss to coat.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: company breakfast
directions: Place
bread
in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cook
sausage
and	crumble over bread.
Beat eggs with milk;
add cheese,
mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage.
Cover and
refrigerate
overnight.
Place in cold oven and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add rest of ingredients and bake in 1-quart casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Stir together juice of lemon, egg yolks and salt; cook until thick.
Cool.
Prepare pineapple, grapes and marshmallows.
Now stir lemon mixture into the whipped cream.
Stir into fruit mixture.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
This salad is not to be tasted or eaten before time is up.

title: dolly's hot seafood dip
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Saute onions and celery with Tabasco until soft.
Drain tuna and shred.
Mix in mayonnaise, bread crumbs, half and half, 1 cup cheese, pepper and almonds.
Stir in onions and celery mixture, spoon into 3 to 4-quart casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: fresh apple pie cake
directions: Peel and slice apples thinly into a 9-inch (2-inch deep) pie pan (or glass layer cake pan).
Mix sugar (1/2 cup) and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Add orange juice (or milk), egg, water and melted butter (or margarine).
Mix until smooth with wooden spoon.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: corn chowder
directions: Put potatoes, onions and celery in a small amount of water. Cook until tender.
Add 2 cups corn, ham, milk and soup.
Stir well while heating.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Simmer ground beef, water and vinegar for 30 minutes.
Add catsup, mustard, sugar, salt and onion.
Cook on low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve on hot dogs or hamburger buns.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray iron skillet with nonstick buttery flavored Pam.
Bake at 450° about 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: indian summer apple cake
directions: Blend together eggs, oil, and sugar until creamy.
Add flour, a small amount at a time, blending well after each addition. Batter will be stiff.
Fold in apples, coconut, and pecans.
Place in greased and floured 10 inch tube pan;
bake at 350 degrees about one hour or until wooded pick inserted in center of cake comes out
clean.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes; remove cake.

title: cherry delight
directions: Place whole can of crushed pineapple (undrained) on bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan.
Spread can of pie filling on top of pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Melt margarine and pour over the mix, then pour nuts on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: white irish soda bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Gradually add sour milk or buttermilk.
Put into prepared pan and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Take dressing mix; pour in sour cream, onion, basil and oregano.
Mix well.
Stir in cooked spinach; chill 1 hour.
Serve with raw vegetables or any type of wheat crackers.

title: quick and easy baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake, covered, in greased casserole at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil.
Add 3 tablespoons of flour until it gets brown.
Throw in everything except meat. Cook for 20 minutes.
Take bay leaves out and reheat for 5 minutes more.
Then add meat.
Meanwhile, have your rice cooked to mix in when done cooking.

title: prune bar cookies
directions: Chop prunes.
Add to chopped nuts with brown sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix.
Fold into well beaten eggs.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pan for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut into 25 pieces.
Roll in confectioners powdered sugar, if desired.

title: window cleaner
directions: Combine and put into a spray bottle.
Shake before using.

title: a wonderful marinating sauce
directions: Simmer all this for several minutes.
Then store in refrigerator.
Meat marinated in this doesn't burn easily as it does hot have tomato sauce in it.
Very good for any kind of meat. I soak my meat about 1 hour before cooking.

title: raspberry slush
directions: Combine pineapple, lemonade, lemon juice, powdered punch, sugar and raspberries in a large container.
Add enough water to make 2 gallons.
Place in freezer and freeze.
About 2 hours before serving, remove from the freezer.
Using a potato masher or pastry mixer, "slush it," then mix in the pop.

title: beef quiche
directions: Brown the meat; drain and set aside.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in the meat, grated cheeses, onion, salt and pepper.
Turn into the pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: oatmeal carmelitas
directions: Melt caramel topping, combined with 1/4 cup flour.
Combine remaining ingredients except chocolate chips and pecans in mixing bowl.
Press half of crumbs into bottom of greased 13 x 9 pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans and spread caramel topping on cooked crumbs. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: wassail
directions: Place spices in a spice ball or bag.
Combine all ingredients. Cover and simmer at least 45 minutes.

title: best-ever hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes until thickened.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla stirring until smooth and glossy.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add whipping cream, eggs and flour (alternately).
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan in a cold oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bucket of dirt
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Mix pudding, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Blend Oreos to crumbs, then layer in pail, starting with crumbs, then pudding and ending with crumbs.

title: asparagus casserole(an extra easy side dish)
directions: Empty the drained asparagus into an ovensafe casserole dish. Spoon soup evenly over asparagus.
Bake at 350° until mixture bubbles, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cheese and bake another 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Spread chicken on bottom of dish.
Mix celery, soup, water chestnuts, mushrooms and mayonnaise together.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with melted butter. Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain the peach syrup into a saucepan.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices and boil 5 minutes.
Add peaches and simmer 5 minutes. Allow fruit to stand in syrup overnight.
Serve chilled.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Mix.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Bake in greased and floured (2) loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until done.

title: cheese pie
