directions: Partially bake pie shell.
Sprinkle all of the Monterey Jack, half of the Cheddar and the chilli peppers in shell.
Beat remaining ingredients together and add to pie shell mixture. Sprinkle remainder of Cheddar on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes, or until crust is brown.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, rice bran, apple fiber and salt.
Or you could do this in a food processor.
Add milk all at once; stir until ingredients are just combined.
If you are doing this in a food processor, pulse the machine a few times just until dough is combined.
If the dough seems a little dry, sprinkle on a tablespoon of water and work it in.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add Cool Whip and stir well.
Pour into glass 13 x 9-inch serving dish and freeze.
Salad can be made 2 to 3 weeks in advance and frozen.
When served, let thaw, then cut into square pieces.
Pretty to serve.

title: old fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in.
Chill.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of pan with broth and pepper.
Mix flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and pour over flour mixture.
Bake in a moderate oven until crust browns.
(I like to use 2 cups of chicken broth as it makes more gravy.)

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar well. Add slightly beaten egg yolks. Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add alternately with flour to which the salt has been added. Fold in egg whites. Add coconut, nuts and vanilla. Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chile rellenos
directions: Roast and peel peppers.
Slit them down the center, lengthwise and fill with both kinds of cheese.
Seal and roll in flour. Continue until all peppers are done.
Separate eggs and whip whites until medium peaks form.

title: papa john's portuguese malasadas
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add cream, butter, flavorings and yeast.
Allow dough to rise, work down and allow to rise a second time.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a baking dish, peel tamales and slice in half lengthwise.
Place layer of tamales, 1/2 can corn and top with 4 slices cheese.
Repeat 1 more layer.
Bake in oven for 1 hour or until cheese melts on top.

title: lime and sour cream pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar with cornstarch and lime peel in medium saucepan and mix well.
Add lime juice and stir until smooth. Blend in half and half and butter.
Place over medium heat and stir until mixture thickens and starts to boil.
Remove from heat and let cool, stirring occasionally.
Fold in sour cream.
Turn into pie shell.
Combine whipping cream and sugar.
Whip until soft peaks.
Spread atop pie.

title: shrimp diane
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet; add garlic.
Lightly saute. Add cubed tomatoes and juice from can; cook 1 minute.
Add wine, salt, fresh black pepper, basil and oregano.
Cook over moderate heat for 10 minutes.
Heat remaining olive oil in a separate skillet.
Saute shrimp for 1 minute, turning once.
Sprinkle with red pepper flakes; remove from heat.
Spoon shrimp and pan juices into a large baking dish.
Crumble Feta cheese over shrimp.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Just before serving, bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 400° oven until sizzling.
Serve over cooked linguine.

title: honey lemon rhubarb pie
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar, flour and lemon rind; mix well. Blend in honey. Put the pie crust in a pie pan and fill with mixture. Put top crust on and seal edges. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: skillet squash au gratin
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add summer squash, onion, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Cook, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes or until squash is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and soy sauce, if desired.

title: macaroni with seasoning salt
directions: Put 5 rice in a bowl and put in the microwave and push the buttons for 38 pounds.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Crush cookies with a rolling pin or in blender until you have 2 cups.
Mix with cinnamon and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.
Beat sugar with eggs until light and fluffy; add cream cheese gradually, beating well after each addition.
Melt the chocolate and add to the egg mixture, along with vanilla and sour cream, beating constantly.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Pour mixture into chilled pie dish and bake at about 350° for 45 minutes.
Chill overnight.
Serves 20.

title: delicious chicken
directions: Boil chicken. Saute mushrooms in butter.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Pour soup over the chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and top with mushrooms. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: paul's potato salad
directions: Boil clean unpeeled potatoes and eggs together until potatoes are to desired firmness.
Cool potatoes and eggs in cool water until comfortable to handle.
Rub the peeling off potatoes using fingers (faster than with knife!).
Remove eggshells from eggs. Dice or mash eggs and potatoes in large bowl along with rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill (or serve room temperature) and serve.
Even better the next day!

title: non-fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening together with hand pastry blender. Beat egg in separate container and add water and beat together. Add this mixture to dry ingredients.

title: cheesy pasta
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute garlic and add pasta and cheese.
Mix on low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve on plate and top with your favorite sauce.

title: triple good bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In medium saucepan, combine the first 4 ingredients (raisins, milk, etc.) Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat; cool slightly and set aside. Beat margarine, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; blend until evenly mixed and crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of prepared pan. Spread raisin mixture to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Sprinkle with remaining oat mixture; pat lightly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; cut into 1 x 2-inch bars.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to beet juice to make 2/3 cup liquid.
Combine cornstarch and pepper in saucepan.
Add liquid and vinegar.
Stir until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute, stirring.
Add sliced beets and sugar.
Heat through.

title: 1 dish bistro stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, blend soup mix with water.
Boil and continue boiling, stirring for 1 minute until thickened.
Add chicken.
Cut into strips and add partially thawed and drained vegetables (ex. broccoli, cauliflower and carrots).
Cook, uncovered, stirring frequently for 5 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over hot rice.
tags: recipe secrets herb with garlic soup mix

title: mamaw's raw pepper relish
directions: Chop all together.
Add 1/2 cup salt to vegetable mixture. Let stand 2 hours.
Drain off juice.
Mix 6 cups of sugar and 1 teaspoon celery seed.
Mix all; put in jars unsealed.

title: slow-cooked mac "n" cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain. Place in a 3-quart slow cooker.

title: vinaigrette sauce
directions: Mix together the vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper, then slowly add the olive oil.
If the sauce is too thick, add some water.
Serve with asparagus, salad or your favorite vegetable.

title: plain pastry or pie shell
directions: For pie shell add 1/2 cup sugar and 1 egg.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in oats.
Drop from teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients together for 3 minutes. Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water. Add to mixture. Put into freezer to thicken. Whip cream to a peak, then beat in cream cheese and add to jello. Mix all. Refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream crescents
directions: Heat sour cream in top of double boiler, until slightly yellow around edges.
Soften yeast in water, let stand 5-10 minutes.
Put butter, suger, and salt in a large bowl, immediately pour sour cream over ingredients in boel and stir until butter is melted. Cook to luke warm.
Blend 1 cup flour into sour cream mixture beating until smooth, stir softened yeast, and add to flour mixture, mixing well.
Add 1 cup of remaining flour and beat until smooth.
Thoroughly beat in eggs and remaining flour.
Cover bowl and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Divide dough into 4 parts. On a lightly floured surface, roll each portion into a round (1/4 inch thick).
Cut each round into 12 wedged shape pieces.
Roll up beginning at the wide end.
Place rolls on greased sheets with points underneath.
Curve into crescents.
Let stand in warm place 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Arrange stalks in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch Pyrex baking dish with flowerets facing outward.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with pimento strips.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Crumble uncooked chuck in bottom of 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Add onions, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix soup and milk; pour over top.
Add Tater Tots on top and bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour, or until Tater Tots are brown.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Place in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Top mixture with bread cubes.
Melt butter and pour atop bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix all-bran and boiling water.
Let stand.
Cream Crisco, sugar, eggs and buttermilk.
Add bran mixture.
Add flour, Kellogg's Bran, salt and soda.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Shape meatball mixture into balls.
Brown in a skillet, then drain off grease.
Place in crock-pot.

title: ann's old fashioned egg custard
directions: In a large 10-inch glass pie plate, melt margarine; set aside. In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, one at a time, with a fork. Add sugar; stir well.
Add flour; stir well.
Add flavoring and stir.
Add milk; mix and pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; turn down to 300° and bake 30 more minutes.
Cool at least 2 hours before cutting.

title: tuna ring
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in jello mold.
Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast, cinnamon, and lemon peel; blend well.
In small saucepan, heat water, milk and butter until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquid and egg to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed with electric mixer until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand stir in 3 to 4 cups flour until dough pulls cleanly away from sides of bowl. Stir 1 cup raisins into dough.
On floured surface, knead in 1 to 2 cups flour until dough is smooth and elastic with blisters under the surface, about 10 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl; cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel.
Let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, about 1 hour.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Mix juice and flour.
Add sugar; mix and add pineapple and cheese.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well the eggs, sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Fold in 1 cup coarsely chopped nuts.
Bake in 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Keeps well and very good.

title: v-8 turkey soup
directions: Brown turkey with onions and add to a large kettle with the other vegetables and juice.
Cook until the vegetables are tender. Water or chicken broth may be added if too thick.
Freezes well. I use zucchini, carrots, potatoes, green beans, onion, peas and celery.

title: luau casserole
directions: Squeeze moisture from vegetable. Combine all ingredients except vegetable. Beat until smooth. Fold in chopped vegetable. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Let stand until firm.

title: homemade chili
directions: Chop onion and garlic (fine), browning in shortening.
Add chili powder and bay leaves.
Add meat.
Add puree, mashed tomatoes and water, then cook slowly for 1/2 hour, or until meat is done.
Thicken with 1/2 cup flour or enough to thicken it. Salt to taste.

title: american applesauce cake
directions: Combine all ingredients down to cloves on low speed of mixer, then on high until well blended.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with fresh vegetables...cucumbers, carrots, celery etc or with chips as a dip.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Mix altogether.
Spread into 2 loaf pans, greased.
Bake slowly at 275° for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Press top with fork that has been dipped in flour to prevent sticking.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned on top, 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: delightfully different chicken pie
directions: Melt margarine in frypan over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown 2 minutes.
Add broth; stir until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in chicken, water chestnuts and parsley.
Cool.
Make rice shell.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup olives in rice shell.
Pour chicken mixture in.
Top with remaining olives.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In frying pan, melt butter.
Stir in olive oil, lemon juice, scallions, garlic, salt and pepper.
Place shrimp in the frying pan.
Toss around until coated with mixture and slightly pink.

title: triple cheese potato bake
directions: You will also need 1 Reynolds| Pot Lux| cookware, 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: white punch
directions: Pour into punch bowl and serve.
One gallon equals 32 cups.

title: holiday cut outs
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs and flour which has been sifted twice with salt and baking powder.
Add extract. Divide dough into 3 balls and wrap in foil.
Place in refrigerator and chill.
Roll cookies thin and cut into shapes.
Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: asparagus chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts in butter, then place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the soup, sour cream and mushrooms; pour 1/4 of this mixture over the chicken breasts.
Make a layer of asparagus spears.
Cover with 1/2 Parmesan cheese.
Add remainder of soup mixture; cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: pot roast
directions: Peel and slice vegetables.
Place roast and vegetables in slow cooker.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add water.
Cook until roast and vegetables are tender.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel off skin of eggplant.
Slice into medium slices, a little less than 1/4 inch thick.
Place in a colander and let drain for a few hours.
Dip slices in flour, then into batter of eggs, salt, pepper, minced garlic, Romano cheese and chopped parsley. Dip slices into bread crumbs, then into flat dish lined with waxed paper.
Use wax paper between each layer.
After all slices are breaded, place in refrigerator for at least 4 - 5 hours or preferably overnight.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil and drain potatoes and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: walnut wafers
directions: Mix in order given and drop by teaspoons 2-inches apart onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake in a hot oven 7 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven. Cool 1 minute before taking from the pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and pudding. Fold in Cool Whip.
Add fruit and nuts. Refrigerate.

title: h.r.e.s.  cafeteria rolls
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix all dry ingredients in mixer bowl using dough hook.
Blend well.
Mix oil and 1 cup of water and pour into the dry ingredients and blend. Add warm water until dough is wet, but stiff.
Mix on high until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Cover bowl and let dough rise to double in size.
Punch down and knead 2 to 3 minutes.
Form rolls by pinching off 2-ounce pieces.
Place on lightly oiled baking sheet.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease an 11 x 15-inch pan and sprinkle with nuts and coconut. Prepare cake mix as directed on box and pour into pan. Melt margarine and cream cheese together.
After melted, stir in powdered sugar. Spoon over top of cake mixture. Cook at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: shaker pumpkin loaves
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until light and fluffy, then beat in pumpkin.
In separate bowl, sift dry ingredients together.
Beat dry into wet until it is blended well.
Divide batter between 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake for 60 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: old-fashioned spanish bar applesauce cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Stir in applesauce, flour mixture, raisins and nuts.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: maple syrup
directions: Bring to boil on high (4 minutes) the sugars and cold water. Boil slow for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add maple flavoring.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from clams and pour over vegetables.
In small pan, add enough water to cover vegetables.
Simmer until tender.

title: creamy potato and ham bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine the potatoes, peas and ham.
In a small bowl, mix the flour, parsley, salt and pepper into soup.
Pour over potato mixture and blend well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish sprayed with butter-flavored cooking spray.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer in a large bowl the lettuce (broken up in bite size), sliced onions, cut up cauliflower and bacon bits.
Sprinkle the sugar.
Spread the Miracle Whip. Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese. Cover tightly and refrigerate 4 hours to overnight. Toss before serving.

title: nestle fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray pan with Pam.
Pour in ingredients and put in freezer for 30 minutes.

title: bev's cheese ball
directions: In a bowl, mix by hand the cream cheese and dry Ranch dressing. Shape into ball; wrap in foil and chill overnight.

title: venison or beef roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast and brown well.
Add all ingredients and roast in oven at 325° for approximately 2 1/2 hours or until done. For best results, use a cooking bag.
Leftover juices make an excellent gravy.

title: coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13 pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, pie filling and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 cake batter in pan. Sprinkle 1/2 sugar mixture on batter.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake 35 minutes or until done.

title: green pea soup
directions: Cover the green peas with hot water to which the sliced onion has been added and cook until the peas can be mashed.
Mash the peas and add the one pint of hot water.
Blend the margarine and flour and cook a minute or so with constant stirring, but do not brown.
Add the peas, then the milk and cream.
Season to taste with salt and white pepper and allow to boil up once.
Strain and serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat white sugar, eggs, Crisco, brown sugar, salt and molasses well, then add sour milk, soda, cinnamon, flour, applesauce, baking powder and allspice.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in loaf pan.
Top with whipped cream to serve.

title: orange dessert
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and heat slowly, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in crumbs, cereal and chopped nuts.
Press half of crumb mixture into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, reserving remaining mixture for topping.
Heat undiluted orange juice.
Add marshmallows, stirring until they are melted.
Cool until mixture begins to thicken, then whip until light and fluffy. Whip cream and fold into orange mixture.
Pour orange mixture over crumb layer.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze until firm. Serves 15.

title: sugar and spice snack
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan with shortening.
Mix snacks and nuts in large bowl.
Beat egg whites, orange juice, sugar and cinnamon in small bowl, using wire whisk or hand beater until foamy.
Pour over snack mixture and stir until evenly coated.
Spread in pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes until light brown and crisp.
Cool; store in airtight container.
Yields about 10 cups snack.

title: cranberry pork chops(easy, tasty and festive)
directions: Brown chops in bacon drippings; season with salt and pepper. Meanwhile, mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Place chops in a baking dish, spread with cranberry mixture and cover.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Serve with baked sweet potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: butternut cake
directions: Mix all together. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or can bake in oblong baking pan for 45 minutes.

title: key lime fudge
directions: Line 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with foil, extending foil over edges of pan; butter foil. Set aside. Stir baking pieces and condensed milk in heavy, large saucepan over low heat just until pieces are melted and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in lime peel and lime juice. Stir in 1 cup Macadamia nuts; spread mixture evenly into the prepared pan. If desired, sprinkle a few coarsely chopped Macadamia nuts on top. Cover and chill for 2 hours or until firm. Lift fudge from pan using edges of foil. Peel off foil. Cut into pieces. Store in airtight container at room temperature for up to 1 week or in the freezer for up to 2 months. Makes 2 1/2 pounds (64 servings).

title: salmon and spaghetti casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter; stir in flour.
Add chicken broth, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add sherry and reserved liquid.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cream and blend well. Remove from heat.
Saute mushrooms in remaining 1/4 cup butter in small skillet until tender.
Add to sauce and mix half of sauce with cooked spaghetti and place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine salmon with remaining sauce and pour over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until brown. Serve hot.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in ungreased baking dish. Dice American cheese on top.
Add crushed potato chips.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk, then sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well and add vanilla.
Chill 20 minutes.
Roll very thin on floured surface.
Cut and bake at 400° until brown.

title: bacon and horseradish dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: rice dish
directions: Cook rice as directed.
In skillet, saute onion, peppers, squash, carrots and broccoli.
Add cubed, cooked chicken or pork. Add all of mixture to rice.
Use a little soy sauce for flavor. Really good!

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over the oatmeal. Let stand 20 minutes. Mix the margarine, white sugar, brown sugar, eggs, flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and vanilla. Add oatmeal. Mix and bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix well; top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with buffet bread or crackers.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix dough; divide into two loaves.
Wrap in wax paper and put in refrigerator for 2 or 3 hours or it can be frozen.
Slice thin and bake at 325° until light brown.

title: candied carrots
directions: Set out a small baking dish.
Wash carrots and scrape.
Cook whole carrots 15 to 25 minutes or until just tender.
Meanwhile, combine brown sugar, water and margarine in small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Drain carrots and place in baking dish.
Cover with sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until carrots are completely glazed.
Baste occasionally.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese in bowl.
Add sausage and Bisquick.
Mix until dough gets very stiff.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 400° until done or brown.
Turn 2 times 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 80 balls.

title: seasoned oyster crackers for snacking(just like potato chips, it's hard to eat only one!)
directions: Shake all ingredients together in a brown paper bag.
Let stand in brown paper bag for 24 hours.
Store in tins or tightly sealed containers.

title: ginger creams
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to butter mixture alternately with water.
Spread onto 2 jelly roll pans, 11 x 16-inch.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Frost and cut into squares.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 40 to 45 cheese balls.

title: bar-be-que spareribs
directions: Put country style spareribs in roaster (as many as you want). Add salt, lemon pepper, onion flakes and water.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Bring milk to full rapid boil.
Stir in cornmeal.
Cook until very thick, stirring constantly, to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Beat eggs well.
Add to cornmeal mixture with salt, butter and baking powder.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Pour into well-greased 1-quart round casserole.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: honey ham tortilla rolls
directions: With electric mixer, beat ham and cream cheese together until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, green onion and honey.
Spread 1/4 cup ham mixture on each flour tortilla starting from one edge.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 to 8 hours before serving.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Place lettuce and onions in a salad bowl; set aside.
In a skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; set aside.
In the drippings, combine all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Immediately pour over salad.
Crumble bacon and add to salad; toss well.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hot german green bean salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove half of fat.
Add onion, vinegar and sugar.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Add reserved liquid to beans and vinegar mixture. Heat through and serve hot.
Yields 4 servings.

title: jumbo shrimp in spicy wine sauce
directions: In a frying
pan,
saute
the shrimp in olive oil for 1 minute,
sprinkle
with
jalapeno
and red pepper flakes.
Add lemon juice
and
wine
to	pan
and cook shrimp, covered over medium heat
for
more
minutes or until shrimp turns pink. Remove shrimp
to a serving bowl.
Strain the sauce and reduce it over
high	heat
to make 1/2 cup.	Pour sauce over shrimp. May be served hot or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tennessee fruit cake
directions: Mix butter, eggs, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla together. Mix together the flour, baking powder, fruits and pecans.
Add this to butter mixture.
Pour into tube pan.
Place in a cold oven; bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: julia's coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder together. Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Add flour and sour cream by alternating.

title: amigos party wings(guatemala)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 F. Mix dressing and chiles in a blender until smooth. Transfer to a small bowl, chill. Combine flour and taco mix in a shallow dish, mix well. Stir in oil until mixed well. If using wings remove tips first. Coat chicken with mixture on all sides. Place on slightly greased cookie pan. Bake for 15 minutes, turn over and bake an additional 15 minutes, or until chicken is tender. Mix parsley in with ranch dressing. Use dressing as a dipping sauce.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Peel apples and slice thinly.
Put into saucepan with water and raisins. Cover and cook 15 minutes until soft.
Cut bread into fingers and arrange half in a pie dish, buttered side down.
Cover with apple mixture, then bread butter side up. Top with sugar and spices. Bake 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding and cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients in a 9-inch pan.
Stir in milk and melted butter.
Mix together in a separate bowl 1/2 cup white sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle over mixture in pan.
Do not stir.
Pour water over this mixture; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top this layer dessert with ice cream or Cool Whip for an extra treat.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add milk, oil and vanilla. Mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: In a large boiler, heat peanut butter, Karo and sugar over medium heat until warm.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Stir until Rice Krispies are mixed in well.
Place on buttered sheets.
Cut and serve.

title: banana breakfast smoothie
directions: Process all ingredients in a blender, stopping to scrape down sides.
Pour mixture into chilled glasses.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, cheese, onions, garlic powder and pepper.
Toss with potatoes and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Crumble 1/2 pound cooked bacon.
Cover casserole with bacon and sliced green olives.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Peel and cut potatoes and carrots.
Salt and pepper chicken. Arrange chicken in casserole dish.
Place potatoes and carrots in dish around chicken.
Then add cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups on top of ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage with cabbage, sweet potatoes(makes 4 servings)
directions: Stir chicken broth and mustard in deep 12-inch skillet. Add sweet potatoes and onions. Reduce heat to medium. Cover and cook about 5 minutes until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally. Add smoked sausage and cabbage. Cover and cook 15 minutes longer, stirring once or twice until potatoes are tender and cabbage is crisp-tender. Stir in apples. Cover and simmer 3 minutes until apple is crisp-tender.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: meme's spice prune cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients together and put into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients just before serving.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Line cupcake pans with liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fill the liners 3/4 full with cheese mixture.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Top each with spoonful of filling and 1 teaspoon nuts.
Chill.

title: salsa cruda
directions: In food processor (you can skip dicing steps), process peppers, salt, garlic, oregano and cumin on "momentary" until finely chopped.
Quarter onion.
Add to mixture and dice.
Add 1/2 cup V-8 (hot) and tomatoes (quartered) and process until diced.
Add vinegar and cilantro.
Process briefly.
Yields 2 cups.

title: party mints
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Add powdered sugar until mixture is stiff enough to work with.

title: triple layer chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup cocoa, sugar and butter.
Press firmly into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat Eagle Brand milk, flour, remaining 1/4 cup cocoa, egg, vanilla and baking powder.
Add walnuts.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Top with chocolate chips.
Bake 20 minutes or until set. Cool.
Store, covered, at room temperature.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese, garlic powder and pepper.
Add broccoli and carrot.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Cover; cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Use double boiler.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and mix.
Add flour and cocoa.
Mix.
Add milk and water.
Cook until thick. Stir occasionally.
When thick, add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Beat egg whites.
Put on top of pie.
Bake at 375° until golden.
Makes 3 pies or 2 deep dish pies.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Peel and slice.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl and bake at 350° for 1 hour (uncovered).

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix all together and put in refrigerator.

title: hamburg delight casserole
directions: Brown meat in hot shortening and add seasonings, onion, carrots, celery, green pepper and tomato soup.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add corn, olives, mushroom soup and spaghetti.
Pour into baking dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350` for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour; press into jelly roll pan.
Prick all over with fork.
Chill 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake 25 additional minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Yield:
72 cookies. These are better if stored in a tin box for several days. Cookies get sweeter with age.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Beat eggs and add the milk and stir into dry ingredients. Mix well.
Add the sliced apples.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into hot oil and fry.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Spoon into dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine Bisquick mix, milk and eggs; beat until smooth.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well a baking sheet.
Place vinegar in measuring cup; add enough evaporated milk to vinegar to make 1 cup.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla, blending well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add milk mixture and dry ingredients alternately to creamed mixture, stirring well after each addition.
Stir in chopped nuts

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook, drain, rinse and cool spaghetti.

title: italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a screw-top jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously to blend well.
Store covered in refrigerator. Shake well before using.

title: crock-pot cowboy stew
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 12 to 15 hours.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Spray inside of double grocery bag with Pam.
Combine brown sugar, margarine, salt, cream of tartar and white syrup for 3 minutes on stove or 2 minutes in microwave.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir.

title: homemade champagne
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake at 350° until done.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Cok rice according to directions on box.
Rinse rice with cold water.
Drain well.
Put into bowl.
Add sugar; let set.
Drain pineapple.
Add to rice; stir in marshmallows.
Beat 1 container whipping cream with sugar (1/4 cup) and vanilla (1/2 to 1 teaspoon).
Fold into rice.
Let set in refrigerator overnight or several hours.

title: applesauce cakes
directions: Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Roll in butter and then into sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Cook bacon until crispy.
Pop out stems on mushrooms.
Mix cream cheese and bacon.
Fill tops of mushrooms with cream cheese mixture.
Grease cookie sheet with bacon grease. Place mushrooms on pan and bake for 20 minutes.

title: chocktaw poke greens(modern)
directions: Pick tender young shoots; boil in water to cover.
Pour off water and rinse.
Add water to cover and simmer until tender. Drain well.
Toss with bacon drippings and serve at once.

title: jean's chicken casserole
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 2 x 13-inch pan.
Spread diced chicken on bottom.
Spread Stove Top evenly over chicken, then cheese and then pour mixture of soup and milk over stuffing and cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for 10 minutes. Serve.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs; add applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Dredge raisins and nuts in flour and fold in.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave peanut butter rocky road
directions: Combine chocolate and peanut butter chips in a large glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on High until melted.
Blend in remaining ingredients in order listed. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Let stand at room temperature before cutting.

title: crawfish fettucine
directions: Cook fettucine according to directions.
Melt margarine in a large pan; saute onion, bell pepper and celery until golden.
Stir in soups, garlic and sherry.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and crawfish.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over cooked fettucine.
Serves 6.

title: kay's corn and sour cream
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft; blend in flour and salt. Cook bacon and drain.
Gradually add sour cream to first mixture, stirring constantly.
Heat to boiling; add corn.
Bring to boil; fold in 1/2 cup crumbled bacon.
Turn into serving dish; garnish with remaining bacon.
Can be fixed ahead and cooked in 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until hot.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well in a large bowl.
Store in a tight container.
Makes 1 gallon of dry ingredients.
Mix 1/4 to 1/3 cup of mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: cheesy chicken and rice
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet.
Add chicken; cook until browned.
Remove chicken.
Add broth, 1/2 cup water and broccoli. Stir.
Heat to a boil.
Stir in rice and cheese.
Top with chicken; cover.
Cook on low heat for 5 minutes or until cooked through.
Gently stir until cheese is melted.

title: swiss cheese broccoli
directions: Grease a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
In 2-quart saucepan over high heat in 1-inch boiling water, heat broccoli and 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling; cover and cook 10 minutes.
Drain.
Set aside.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Make mashed potatoes as directed. Stir in mustard, egg and tuna; shape and roll in butter and bread crumbs. Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with mushroom or tomato sauce.

title: cool and creamy garden wedges
directions: *Use as many and as much as you like.

title: hot cinnamon cocoa
directions: In the top of a double boiler, stir together cocoa, sugar and salt.
Gradually add boiling water.
Place over direct heat and boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and cinnamon sticks and place over boiling water.
Stir and heat 10 minutes. Remove sticks and stir in vanilla.
Beat with a wire whisk to froth milk.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Into a bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and a pinch of salt.
In the top of double boiler, set over simmering water, heat coffee and bourbon for 5 minutes (this removes most of alcohol; baking removes the rest).
Add chocolate and butter, all cut into pieces, and heat the mixture, stirring, until the chocolate and butter are melted and the mixture is smooth.
Remove the pan from the heat and stir in sugar.
Let the mixture cool for 3 minutes and transfer it to the bowl of an electric mixer.
Add the flour mixture to the chocolate mixture, 1/2 cup at a time, beating at medium speed and continue to beat the mixture for 1 minute.
Add the eggs and vanilla and beat the batter until it is smooth.

title: heyward's good for what ails you salad(makes enough for a dozen people)
directions: Mix fruit and sprinkle with lemon juice to prevent darkening. Serve in a large glass bowl.
Good for Potluck suppers.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies and place in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch container.
Pour chocolate syrup on top.
Dip out desired amount of ice cream and spread on top of chocolate.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 25 minutes.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Flatten chicken breasts (place between 2 pieces of plastic wrap and use rolling pin to flatten to uniform thickness).
Dredge breasts in flour with oregano, pepper and salt; shake off excess. Lightly brown in olive oil and butter.
Drain on paper towels. Set aside.
Saute mushrooms in remaining oil; remove from skillet. Pour over breasts.
Add lemon juice, chicken stock and Marsala to skillet and simmer.
Add about 2 tablespoons cornstarch mixed into 1/4 cup water and add to the skillet mixture.
Stir constantly until becomes thick and smooth.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and stir in.
Pour sauce over chicken and mushrooms.
Keep warm until you serve and garnish with lemon slices.

title: sun dill pickles
directions: Pack cukes in jars with all other items, except vinegar and water.
Bring vinegar and water to a boil.
Pour over cukes within 1/2 inch of top.
Seal and set in the sun for 7 to 10 days.
Don't open until 5 weeks later.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Melt jello in hot water and add rest of the ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all above ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Put top crust on.
Bake at 300° for 90 minutes.

title: jeannie and lela's overnight layered salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan layer:
lettuce, celery, onion, water chestnuts and frozen peas.
Top and seal side to side with Miracle Whip salad dressing.
Do not stir together.
Spread on like you were frosting a cake.
Sprinkle with:
sugar, seasoned salt, garlic powder, Parmesan cheese.
Cover and leave overnight.
Just before serving, top with chopped eggs, and chopped crumbled bacon.
Be sure to drain bacon well after cooking it.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Cook beef and onion until meat is browned; drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce and sauce mix; cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with sour cream; sprinkle with cheese.
Unroll crescent rolls and place on top of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: butterfinger trifle
directions: Cook brownies.
Crumble half of brownies in bottom of trifle bowl.
Layer 1/2 crushed Butterfingers, layer vanilla pudding, then layer Cool Whip.
Repeat layers using chocolate pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: low sugar, low-fat fruit salad
directions: Cut up fruit and sprinkle with Equal.
Add peanuts and marshmallows.
Stir in mayonnaise.
When served with nachos, this is a complete meal for 2.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Heat marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Stir until melted.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix creme de menthe and creme de cocoa and most of the Cool Whip.
Fold into cooled marshmallow mixture.
Pour into crust.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate coated fondant balls
directions: Beat butter until soft.
Gradually add sugar and milk alternately.
Divide into several sections, coloring and flavoring as desired (rum, orange, cherry, almond, mint, etc. perhaps a very small amount of vanilla as well).
Chill until good and cold.

title: 6 weeks bran muffins
directions: Mix
cereal,
flour, soda and salt.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs. Beat
well,
then
add
buttermilk.
Mix
dry
and	wet ingredients together.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° for 20 minutes.
Keep
rest of batter in refrigerator as long as 6 weeks. Use as needed.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook the spaghetti as directed and drain. Saute the onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Combine spaghetti, onion and pepper, soup, pimento, chicken and half of the cheese.
Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion. Combine rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry chiffon pie(low fat)
directions: In large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Fold in the whipped topping and 2 cups strawberries.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate for 3 hours or until set.
Garnish with the remaining strawberries.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: a cheap and quick pudding
directions: Beat up 4 eggs; add a pint of milk and a little salt (dash). Stir in the 4 large spoonfuls of flour, a little nutmeg and a little sugar to your taste.
Beat it well.
Pour into buttered teacups (custard dishes) filling them a little more than half full.
Bake in an oven (moderate) for about 15 minutes.

title: deer roast
directions: Use a small roaster with lid.
Place all ingredients in roaster.
Cover and bake at 350° for 4 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: bettie cook's easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger with garlic salt, then drain.
Add oregano; simmer for 30 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Cook noodles, then arrange in pan with alternate layers (meat, cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese ending with Mozzarella on top).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage with hot vinegar dressing
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water until tender, about 10 minutes. Drain.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Stir in vinegar, sugar and salt. Heat and pour over cabbage.
Serve.

title: chess cake
directions: Beat together thoroughly cake mix, egg and butter.
Put on buttered sheet cake pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Spread over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fritters
directions: Stir milk into well beaten eggs.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in fat and mix until well blended.
Cut up fruit or vegetables (see following).
Add to or dip in fritter batter.
Drop into hot fat (375°) and fry until brown.
Drain and serve hot with syrup or gravy.
Yields 12 to 15 small fritters.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and place in 8 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top, cover and bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream peanut butter, oleo, 10x sugar and flavoring.
Mix well. Will be thick.
Roll into balls.
Melt chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate with toothpick.
Always place on foil.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: For Sauce:
Cook onion in the margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix above ingredients together until creamy.
Store in refrigerator.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Saute
celery,	onion
and
peppers
lightly in butter. Remove from pan. Brown beef in same pan.
Drain well to remove fat.

title: okra creole
directions: Chop bacon and fry until crisp.
Remove from drippings.
Chop onion and pepper and cut okra into 1-inch pieces.
Add to bacon drippings and stir-fry until onion is transparent.
Add seasonings and tomatoes and cook about 5 minutes longer.

title: pizza dip and sticks
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Beat in pizza sauce, green onion and oregano. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Use Mozzarella cheese sticks, celery, carrots or wheat crackers for dipping.

title: spring salad
directions: Mix together the sugar, water, turmeric and mayonnaise.
Add celery and onion.
Cook rotini.
Put in colander and drain.
Run cold water over.
After cold, add dressing.

title: champagne punch
directions: Pour all ingredients over ice into punch bowl.
Stir and ladle into cups.
If recipe is doubled you do not need to double the strawberries.

title: apple crisp
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, cut up apples.
Cover with brown sugar and cinnamon which have been combined.
Combine in a bowl the Bisquick, white sugar and oats.
Cut into this one egg.
Put this mixture on top of the apples.
Slice 1 stick of margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until sides are bubbly.

title: paul's hot wings(buffalo)
directions: Heat oil to 400°.
Recommend that you use enough oil to cover wings in deep fryer or electric skillet.
Carefully place in oil. Cover.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour into crust. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: aunt vic's baked beans
directions: Mix beans, sugar, mustard
and
ketchup
in baking pan. Cook bacon in frying pan.
Crumble bacon; add to above mixture along with grease.
Lay remaining bacon
on top of beans.
Lay onion in middle of pan.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 2 hours.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle rice over margarine.
Place chicken on the rice.
Season with salt and pepper as you like.
Spoon the undiluted soup over the chicken and rice.
Pour the water over all.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Place all ingredients in pot with just enough water to cover. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
If there is too much liquid, remove cover and cook until most of it is evaporated.
Yields 4 servings. Good served with rice.

title: new england sponge cake(this was my mother's recipe)
directions: Beat eggs vigorously.
Add sugar and continue to beat rapidly. Add boiling water, beating constantly, the more the better.
Add flavoring (vanilla may be used).
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to first mixture and continue to beat rapidly.
Pour into well-greased pan and bake in 350° oven about 35 to 40 minutes. Can be baked in tube pan or 13 x 9-inch if you want to use it for shortcake.

title: coated pecans
directions: Roast pecans 10 to 12 minutes at 300°.
In large saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Cook on high approximately 2 minutes, or until forms soft ball in water.
Remove from heat. Add pecans and stir by hand until sugared.
Pour out on wax paper and separate.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Crumble yeast; add sugar, salt and water.
Beat in egg.
Add 1/2 of the flour and beat.
Add 1/2 of the butter and the other 1/2 flour.
Let rise to double original size.
Punch down, cover and place in refrigerator.
Dough may be used as needed for rolls. Keeps about a week.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli tops and drain.
Combine with other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 2-quart dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top and brown.

title: spicy applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times. Mix eggs, sweetener and fruit liquid.
Beat at top speed of mixer until fluffy and thick (about 10 minutes).
Decrease speed; add applesauce and beat 3 minutes.
Carefully fold in dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Place 1/4 almond on each cookie.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Cookie will spring back at light touch when done.
(May be placed under broiler to give deeper finish.)

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar; set aside.
Cream remaining 1 cup butter.
Slowly add 2 cups sugar, beating well.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Add vanilla.
Combine 2 3/4 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Dredge blueberries in 1/4 cup flour.
Stir to coat well.
Fold blueberries into batter. Pour into
pan
and
bake
at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool and remove from pan.
Let cool completely.

title: broccoli, cauliflower and carrot salad
directions: Cut up the vegetables and mix together.
Mix the mayonnaise, sour cream and Ranch dressing and add to the vegetables.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Add bell pepper, onion and celery to butter; saute until tender.
Add crawfish, green onions and other seasonings.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch dissolved in water; cook long enough to thicken.
Place in 9-inch pie crust and crust cover.
Bake pie in preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes, then lower heat to 375° and cook 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: peanut butter chocolate sandwich cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and 1 cup sugar together.
Add beaten egg and mix well.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Press flat with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While the cookies are cooling, melt chocolate over low heat.
Melt butter in chocolate.
Remove from heat and add hot water.
Then add confectioners sugar gradually, until icing is thick enough (you may not need to use all the sugar).
Add vanilla. Spread icing on top half of the cookies.
Place plain cookies on top of iced cookies to make sandwiches.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: baked popcorn
directions: Fill 1 large roasting pan full of popped corn, free of unpopped kernels.
Combine remaining ingredients in pot.
Heat until it almost comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/4 teaspoon soda and mix well.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: cauliflower cheese soup
directions: Combine water, cauliflower, potatoes, celery, carrots and onion in a large pan; boil for 5 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Set aside.
Melt butter in separate pan over medium heat.
Stir in flour.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and slowly stir in milk.
Return to heat and cook until thickened.
Stir in vegetables with cooking liquid, then stir in cheese until melted.
Use salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli dip and potato topping
directions: Melt butter; add onions and broccoli.
No need to drain broccoli first.
Cook thoroughly over low heat.
Add mushrooms and soups and cook until well heated.
Add cheese and almonds.
This is good served warm with chips or use leftovers on toast for dinner.
Serve over baked potatoes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil 2 chicken breasts until done.
Remove; cool.
Cook spaghetti in same water.
Drain.
Melt margarine.
Add soups, mushrooms, sour cream and garlic powder (if desired) to taste. Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Add chicken and spaghetti. Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
tags: cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup

title: cole slaw
directions: Stir together and pour over chopped cabbage, green pepper, celery and carrots.
Let set overnight.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and oleo to a quick boil (do not scorch). Cook for 6 to 9 minutes at 225° to 230° on thermometer.
Add marshmallow cream and butterscotch morsels.
Stir to melt and blend well together.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten each chicken breast to about 1/4-inch.
Salt and pepper to taste, top with ham.
Add cheese and roll up.
Secure with a toothpick.
Roll in flour.
Melt butter in skillet, add mushrooms and onions.
Saute until tender.
Add water, chicken bouillon, parsley and chives.
Boil.
Add chicken rolls.
Lower heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken and bring sauce to a boil.
Stir in cream.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix and marinate for a couple of hours or overnight in the refrigerator.
Cook in saucepan on high heat with lid on.
Bring to a boil and then lower heat.
Cook until tender, about 45 minutes. Skim off fat.
Bring mixture to a rapid boil and add vinegar or juice from pineapple with 1/2 cup vinegar and pineapple.
Taste sauce and adjust seasonings.
Add 2 to 4 tablespoons more sugar, if desired.
Add remainder of juice from pineapple can.
Make a paste of cornstarch and water and add to boiling mixture.
Boil until thickened, then lower heat to simmer.
Add pineapple chunks.
Place lid on pan and simmer until served.
Yields 6 servings with some leftover.
Leftovers taste better the second day.
Serve with rice.

title: peanut butter pops
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients well.
Roll frozen bananas in mixture.
You can cut bananas in half and insert popsicle stick in each.
Bananas pops may be rolled in chopped peanuts, if desired. Freeze.

title: overnight egg casserole
directions: Cut crust off bread and cut into cubes; set aside.
Combine milk, eggs, salt, mustard and pepper.
Lightly combine together milk mixture, bread crumbs and ham or sausage.
Pour mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish, greased lightly.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Bake in preheated 325° oven about 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: spoon corn bread
directions: Stir meal into 2 cups milk; let come to a boil, stirring constantly, making a mush.
Add balance of milk, well beaten egg, salt, baking powder and butter, melted.
Turn at once into a quart size, well-greased glass baking dish.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 32 minutes, or until done.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan. Combine cake mix and all ingredients in large bowl and beat well. Pour into pan.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until tester shows it's done.
Cool for 10 minutes and turn out of pan.
Glaze with 1 cup powdered sugar and enough hot water to pour.
Pour over cake while cake is hot.

title: harvest cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil and vanilla; mix in about 1/4 of dry ingredients.
Fold in apples, nuts and remainder of dry ingredients, sifted together.
Bake in greased tube pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: danish puff
directions: Blend and mix to a paste the first two ingredients.
Round into a ball and divide in two.
Put into two long strips on ungreased baking sheet.
Then mix the butter, water and almond.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add flour and sugar.
When smooth, add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Divide in two and spread evenly over pastry.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Do not underbake.
Makes 2.

title: sunshine toddy
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan; bring to boiling.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Strain; pour into heated punch bowl.
Float orange slices on top.
Makes 8 servings.
A cheerful pick-up on a blustery day!

title: cheesy cheddar potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, breaking up potatoes if necessary.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hawaiian style veggie mix
directions: Drain pineapple; measure syrup and add water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Combine liquid, butter, pineapple, soy sauce, ginger and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, carrots and chives.
Cover.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: tuna-noodle
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, soup and milk. Cook until thick and bubbly.
Stir in tuna, pimiento and drained noodles.
Turn mixture into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake uncovered at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased loaf pan. Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly. Spread over apples. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Great with vanilla ice cream. Makes 2 generous servings. Can easily be doubled or tripled.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Measure and sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream margarine; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir until mixed.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Fold in dry ingredients and nuts.
Place in a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick sweet dills
directions: Drain pickles.
Slice.
Return to jar.
Bring mixture to a boil, pour over pickles.
Let cool and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream together oleo, white sugar and brown sugar.
Stir in egg, peanut butter, salt, soda, vanilla, flour and oats.
Spread in oblong pan.
Do not grease.
Put in oven and turn on heat at 350°.
Bake 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Let cool for 1 hour and then spread with Betty Crocker chocolate frosting.
After frosting, mix the Icing.

title: easy butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking soda and blend into mixture. You may add anything at this time.
Example: M&M's, raisins, chocolate chips, nuts, etc.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly buttered cookie sheet and pat slightly.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes until lightly browned.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon till crisp.
Chop into small bits.
Add some of bacon grease to potatoes.
Saute onion, celery in remaining grease.
Then mix with potatoes and bacon.
Add water to skillet with vinegar and sugar.
Don't make it too sweet!
Simmer for a few minutes. Add a bit of cornstarch to thicken.
Combine with potato mixture and stir.

title: date balls
directions: Mix together in saucepan the egg, sugar, dates and butter. Simmer on top of stove, approximately 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Let cool one minute.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Shape into balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: devonshire sauce
directions: Mix well by hand.
Do not use blender.
Spoon over the strawberries or peaches.
Sprinkle nutmeg on lightly.
Enjoy.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine, shortening and sugars until blended.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat until blended.
Add flour.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 12 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: brownies
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour mixture with creamed mixture. Add nuts.
Grease and flour 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: weed's salad
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and salt.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add to Jell-O and refrigerate until at least soupy.
Fold in cheese and whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together; cut in butter until it looks like oatmeal.
Chill 1 hour and then press into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: In small saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add milk. Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Serve warm or cold.
Refrigerate any remaining sauce.
Makes 8 (2 tablespoon) servings.

title: poached lobster delights and garden vegetables(fish - low calorie)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook and stir on medium heat, until mixture thickens and boils.
Add mushrooms, lobster and vegetables.
Cover; reduce heat.
Simmer about 10 minutes or until tender-crisp, stirring once.
Stir in lime juice and margarine.
Makes 4 servings, 111 calories per serving.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions in three 8-inch layers.
Cool.
Take sweet milk, 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon vanilla flavoring and pour this over each layer as you ice them (prick with fork).

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; mix wet ingredients.
Combine both.
Add nuts.
Turn into ungreased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve frosted or plain.

title: crab cakes
directions: Pick over crabmeat to remove shells.
Add all other ingredients except bread crumbs and toss lightly.
Shape into cakes, roll in bread crumbs and fry quickly in hot fat.
Makes 6 to 8 cakes.

title: fruit and nut scones
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine. Beat eggs and milk together, then add date crystals to soften. Stir egg mixture into flour mixture; blend well.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board and pat to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut into 12 scones; place on greased baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown onions in oil; add ground beef.
Stir with fork until brown.
Add all but beans.
Stir well and add beans.
Put in casserole dish; bake at 400° in oven approximately 30 minutes.

title: roasted serrano salsa
directions: Cook Serrano peppers in a cast iron skillet on high heat 10 minutes or until blackened, turning peppers.
Combine Serrano peppers, tomatoes and next 7 ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: grilled fish
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Spray the vegetable oil over the baking sheet 3 times to coat.
Put the cornmeal, thyme and basil on a large plate and mix well.
Sprinkle 1/8 teaspoon of the garlic powder, 1/8 teaspoon of the lemon pepper and 1 teaspoon of the blackening seasoning on each of the catfish fillets.
Coat the fillets thoroughly with the cornmeal mixture and transfer them to the prepared baking sheet.
Dust each fillet with 1/8 teaspoon of the paprika.
Coat the catfish lightly with the cooking spray. Place the baking sheet on the bottom shelf of the oven.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Reduce the heat to 350° and bake for about 5 minutes more, until the crust is golden and the fish flakes easily.

title: spaghetti salad supreme
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and cool.
Add to spaghetti, chopped onion, bell pepper, diced tomato and cucumber.
Marinate with Italian seasoning.
Add salad seasonings.
Cover; refrigerate.
Serve cool.

title: low-fat dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Chill overnight.

title: aunt brenda's brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
In a bowl, mix sugar and eggs.
Beat well. Add flour and salt which have been sifted together.
Blend thoroughly. Add melted butter/chocolate mixture. Blend well. Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix. Spread on lightly greased bottoms of 2 shallow 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pans or 1 large shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Do not overbake.
Cut in squares while hot.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: my mother's rolled cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar, milk and vanilla. Add flour, a little at a time.
Roll out a small amount of dough at a time to approximately pie crust thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Decorate with colored sugars, etc. (or frost after baking).
Using a greased cookie sheet, bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: low-fat blend
directions: Mix in blender or by hand.
Can be stored in a food container in the fridge to use by the cup or spoonful in a myriad of ways.

title: pretty holiday divinity
directions: Butter sides of 2-quart saucepan and place first 4 ingredients in.
Cook; stir constantly until sugar dissolves and mix comes to a boil.
Cook to hard ball stage (250°) without stirring.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in gelatin until stiff peaks form.
Pour hot syrup slowly over egg white mixture. Beat constantly at high speed until soft peaks form and mixture starts to lose its gloss.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: mexican hot chocolate
directions: In a large saucepan, combine 1 cup milk, sugar, chocolate and cinnamon.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat until chocolate is melted. Gradually stir in remaining milk. Cook and stir until milk is very hot, almost boiling, but do not boil.
Gradually stir 1 cup of hot mix into eggs, then return all to saucepan. Cook and stir for 2 minutes over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Beat with beater until frothy.
Pour into mugs and top with whipped cream.
Makes 6 (8 ounce) servings.

title: pineapple-mandarin frost
directions: Combine mandarin, pineapple and lime juice and chill thoroughly.
To serve, pour fruit juice mixture into chilled bowl with mandarin Ice Ring:
Carefully pour in carbonated water, swirl gently to mix.
Float scoops of sherbet on top.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cookies from cake mix
directions: Mix well. Add whatever you want to use; white, yellow or chocolate cake mix.

title: toasty breakfast pockets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Using 3-inch Cut-N-Seal, cut 6 circles from cheese slices on Cutting Board. Cut each circle into quarters using My Safe Cutter. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate. Cut the remaining scraps of cheese into small pieces and place in Classic 2-Quart Batter Bowl.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: beef 'n rice skillet
directions: Lightly brown meat and butter in a large skillet.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt and crushed pepper.
Meanwhile, thinly slice onion and pepper.
Add to pan.
Stir in rice.
Saute, over high heat, until rice is lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, mustard and remaining salt.
Mix well.
Boil and simmer 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: berried delight
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press firmly in bottom of cake pan.
Chill.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust. Arrange fruit in even layers.
Using milk, prepare pudding as directed.
Pour over fruit.
Chill overnight.
Before serving, cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Different fruits may be used in place of pineapple (3 sliced bananas, 4 cups sliced peaches or 2 pints strawberries).

title: mother's applesauce cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and egg together.
Dissolve soda into applesauce and add.
Sift flour, cinnamon and cloves with part of flour.
Add to the first mixture.
Add enough flour to make a fairly stiff batter (amount depends upon the thickness of the applesauce).
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: praline supreme
directions: Spoon ice cream onto pie crust.
Place crumbled cookies over ice cream.
Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in bowl.
Blend with mixer on slow speed for 1 minute.
Fold in carton of Cool Whip.
(Save a tablespoon for dollop.) Place Heath crunches over topping and a dollop of Cool Whip for garnish.

title: uncle vern's cole slaw
directions: Chop the first 3 ingredients fine.
Mix the water, sugar and salad dressing together.
Pour dressing over cabbage.
Mix well. Better if sits overnight.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add the egg and milk; mix well and beat until smooth.
Hold finger over bottom of funnel.
Pour in 1/3 cup batter.
Remove finger and let batter drop in a spiral motion in hot oil.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Remove; drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve warm.
Yields 3 large cakes.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Use a 2-cup container.
Pour in cran-orange and enough water (I use orange juice) to make 2 cups. Add to Jell-O plus the celery and nuts.
Pour into mold and enjoy a couple of hours later.

title: dan patrick's crabmeat melts(celebrity favorite)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Top each cracker with 1 tablespoon of the crabmeat mixture.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 36.
These hot and spicy appetizers are fast and easy enough to make as a snack during halftime.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate marshmallow brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix by hand. Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; sift into above mixture. Add milk, a little at a time.
Add nuts.
Grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 10 x 15-inch pan.
While still hot, spread Marshmallow Creme over top.
Let cool.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in pan.
Drain.
Crumble beef and mix with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in a greased casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.
It is better looking if you sprinkle some grated cheese on top before baking.
Freezes well.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Boil slowly until a ball can be formed in cold water.

title: marinara pasta sauce
directions: Heat oil in large pot. Peel and slice garlic and add to oil. Immediately add tomatoes and tomato puree. Do not brown the garlic!

Stir once. Cover and simmer sauce for at least 3 hours, stirring occasionally. The sauce will turn from a bright red to more of an orange color when it is done. Serve over pasta with grated peccerino romano cheese.

title: "prompt" meat and potatoes
directions: Using a small casserole flat dish, layer these ingredients in order of the letters PROMPT.
Grease dish well with butter and begin layer with, potatoes, uncooked rice, chopped onion, raw ground beef, pepper and salt.
Top with tomato sauce.
Bake 400° for 30 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese if desired before serving.
This is an easy and quick recipe.

title: appluscious cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla. Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Blend together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon and fold in apples and walnuts.
Grease and flour a spring-form angel food pan.
Pour in batter and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove carefully as it tends to stick to sides.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients
and pour into baking dish.
If too dry, add a little chicken
broth.
Bake	at
350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash; place a layer.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle grated cheese and diced onions.
Repeat 3 or 4 layers.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Certo.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Ladle into hot jars and seal.
Immediately invert jars for 5 minutes, then turn up right (helps to seal). About 1 hour later, shake jars to mix peppers before completely set.
Great with cream cheese and crackers.
Yields about 6 to 8 half-pints.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mix with crushed crackers and spread on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Place cheese in bowl.
Add half and half to make of spreading consistency.
Stir mustard in.
Spoon into serving dish.
Serve with crackers, vegetables or apples.
Yields 8 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms.

Remove stems and discard. Melt 1/4 c. butter on each of two cookie sheets. Mix all ingredients and stuff. Bake for 45 minutes at 350° making sure the meat is well-cooked. Drain on towels and serve hot.

title: granny's buttermilk salad
directions: Boil pineapple and jello until dissolved.
Cool.
Mix buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix all together; chill and serve.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add the vanilla and water.
Beat well.
Gradually add flour and salt until well blended.
Add pecans and beat until well mixed. Cover and chill for 1 hour.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Drop spoonfuls of sour cream on meat and cover with grated Mozzarella cheese.

title: sunflower seed cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening together.
Add eggs, beating well. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; mix.
Add chocolate chips or raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in oil until transparent and thoroughly cooked. Add broth and black pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Divide into 6 ovenproof casseroles or bowls.
Top each with a slice of toasted French bread.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place in oven or under broiler until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken divine
directions: Boil chicken.
Melt butter and blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth and cook until mix thickens.
Add heavy cream. Stir in cream and wine in pan.
Put all broccoli crosswise.
Pour mix over it.
Put chicken in dish.
Sprinkle cheese over ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all together.
Keep in refrigerator.
Very good with vegetables or chips.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan.
Pour graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over graham crackers.
Then layer remaining ingredients.
Press lightly into milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or golden brown.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients together. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture forms a stiff ball. Add food coloring, if desired. Knead.
Store in refrigerator in a plastic bag or container.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crumble cookies and add milk.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan . Mix cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread this on the crust.
Mix chocolate pudding and milk; spread on top.
Cover with cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine salt, flour and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in pecans or walnuts and chocolate chips.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake one sheet at a time from 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake. Cool for 2 minutes.

title: spicy peaches in syrup
directions: Place peach halves in two 1 quart jars.
In medium saucepan, combine reserved peach syrup, vinegar, cinnamon and allspice. Bring to a boil. Pour syrup over peaches in jar.
Cool.
Cover. Refrigerate at least 8 hours to blend flavors.
Serve as an accompaniment for ham or pork.
Yields 16 servings.

title: last minute rolls
directions: About 1/2 Hour Before Dinner:
Into scalded milk in a large bowl, stir sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool until lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast into warm water in measuring cup.
Stir until dissolved. Stir into lukewarm milk mixture. Add flour.
Stir until well blended, about 1 minute.
