Cover batter with wax paper and towel. Let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until doubled in bulk. Stir well, then beat vigorously about 1/2 minute. Fill greased 3-inch muffin pan cups about 2/3 full. Bake at 400° about 25 minutes. Remove from pans while hot. Makes 1 dozen.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seeds in milk for 2 hours.
Then sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter with vanilla.

Add sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy after each addition. Beating only until smooth after each addition, alternately add dry ingredients in fourths, poppy seed/milk in thirds to creamed mixture.

title: first down dip
directions: Microwave process cheese spread and sour cream in small bowl on HIGH 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute. Stir in remaining ingredients. Serve warm with soft pretzels and vegetable dippers. Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Melt margarine and saute onion until tender.
Add rice, soup and cheese to the onion.
Stir in the drained broccoli and blend all ingredients. Pour into a greased casserole and sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yeast rolls w-r
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat egg; add to yeast and water 1 teaspoon sugar; set aside.
Mix oil, water, sugar, milk and salt together; add to yeast mixture and mix.
Add flour 2 cups at a time until bouncie.
Put in lightly oiled pan; let rise until doubled in bulk or size.
Knead lightly and make into rolls.
Let rise 2 to 3 hours.
Put in warm place.
Do not set over pilot light as they will rise too fast.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Brush with butter and brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, melted margarine, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add coconut last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put into preheated 375° oven.
Bake 10 minutes.
Then lower heat to 300° and bake for approximately 30 minutes or until set and begins to brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower in bite-size pieces.
Toss vegetables with bacon.
Mix sugar, vinegar, onion and mayonnaise. Pour on vegetables and toss.
Add raisins and stir well. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: raisin pie
directions: Soak raisins for half a day in 2 cups of water.
Bring to a boil after soaking.
Add remaining ingredients except corn starch. Thicken with cornstarch with a bit of raisin juice.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 3 cups of dry mix.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Combine chocolate and water; bring to a boil, and stir until chocolate melts. Cool; stir in vanilla and set aside. Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add chocolate mixture; beat until blended. Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; fold into batter. Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9 inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans, and cool completely. Spread coconut-pecan frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake. Garnish with pecans, if desired.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into 2 separate iron skillet and bake at 350° until brown.

title: jello cake
directions: Break up cake and put in a cake pan. Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water and 1 1/2 cups cold water. Mix in strawberries and 1/2 tub Cool Whip. Pour over cake. Add remainder of Cool Whip to top of cake. Refrigerate for 1 to 2 days before serving.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and pumpkin.
Mix egg and vanilla.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonful on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: "happy birthday cake"
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients into bowl.
Add shortening, sugar, 1/2 cup milk, extracts and 1 egg.
Beat 2 minutes on low speed. Add 1/4 cup milk and 2 eggs.
Beat 2 minutes on low speed. Pour into greased layer pans and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Yields 2 (9-inch) round layers.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Brown beef.
Place potatoes and onion in large buttered baking dish.
Add beef.
Mix soup and little milk until smooth and add to meat and potatoes.
Mix together.
Combine tomato sauce, salt, pepper and sugar.
Pour over top of mixture.
Dot with butter. Cover and bake at least 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Place cheese on top.
Return to oven until cheese melts, about 15 minutes.

title: green beans mornay
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish alternately layer beans and onions.
Combine soup, milk and marjoram.
Pour over beans and onions.
Sprinkle top with cheese. Bake uncovered for 20 - 25 minutes.

title: pina coladas
directions: In blender, add 2 1/2 to 3 cups chipped ice, pineapple juice, 3 tablespoons cream of coconut and 1 tablespoon pineapple.
Mix well. Then add 2 1/2 to 3 ounces of rum (size of blender, cap of lid).

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix crab meat, seasoning, salt and baking powder.
Mix egg and mayonnaise; add to crab mixture.
Make into 8 cakes and fry until browned.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute the onion, celery and green pepper in a large skillet or wok.
Cook and stir until the onion is tender, about 3 minutes, using medium-high heat.
Stir in the rice, the soup base and soy sauce.
Cook on low heat, stirring frequently, for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: sweet and savory meat ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and shape into balls.
Brown in skillet and pour off accumulated fat.
Mix other ingredients. Place meat balls into a baking dish and cover with soup mixture. Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: cheese biscuits (red lobster)
directions: Combine Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Combine butter and garlic.
Brush over biscuits while warm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat brown sugar and water. Boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat; add vanilla and margarine. Mix well. Pour a little hot mixture into eggs. Put egg mixture back into pot. Heat together until thickens. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Add pecans. Bake at 350° until browned.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Butter a 2 1/2-quart casserole. Check oysters for shell pieces.
Layer
crushed
crackers,	oysters,
butter, salt and pepper, about
or 3 layers. Pour any oyster juice over top. Scald milk.
Pour over all. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Insert
knife in center;	should come out clean, like a custard
pie. This can be doubled easily; use a larger casserole.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix graham crackers and oleo in 14 x 9 x 2-inch pan for crust. (May use pre-made graham cracker crust.)

title: aunt sally's cocoa drop cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and egg.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Chill 1 hour. Grease sheets.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Have all cheeses at room temperature.
Grate or cut fine American and sharp cheese.
Cream all in electric mixer.
Add garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce while mixing.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Make into 3 or 4 balls.
Roll in chopped nuts or in parsley.

title: sage chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.

title: john wayne's chili cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Remove seeds from chilies and dice. Combine grated cheeses and chilies.
Put in buttered, shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
In another bowl, combine egg yolks, milk, flour, salt and pepper and mix until well blended.
Gently fold egg whites into egg yolk mixture and then pour over cheese mixture.
Using a fork, ooze it through the cheese mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Arrange tomatoes on top and then bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: chop stick casserole
directions: Mix lightly, except save 1 cup noodles for the top.
Put in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: smoky salmon spread
directions: Mix well; shape into ball or log.
Wrap in wax paper and chill (may be frozen).
To serve, roll in chopped pecans or parsley.

title: ice box fruitcake
directions: Melt 1 lb. of marshmallows and can of Carnation milk in double boiler.
Crush 1 lb. box of graham crackers and pecans. (Cut top of box across top so cake can be placed in box once all ingredients are mixed together.) Combine cherries, raisins, and marshmallows.
Mix all ingredients together and put in graham cracker box and let set in freezer for a couple of days.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage in enough water to cover; cook for 2 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and place on cabbage leaves.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Wrap rolls in foil and place in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cider wassail
directions: Simmer all ingredients (put spices in a cloth, if desired) for 20 minutes. Remove spices and serve hot. A few red hot candies may be added to each cup, if desired.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Grease 10-inch tube pan with 2 tablespoons of butter. Sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup of sugar.
Set aside.

title: gourmet turkey dressing
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onions, celery and mushrooms. Pour over torn toasted bread.
Add browned hamburger, eggs, seasonings and chicken broth.
Mix together well.
Stuff turkey or chicken or place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° until top is brown.
Serves 12.

title: mary's persimmon beer
directions: Place pine straw at the bottom of the crock.
Fill crock with whole persimmons, leaving a 3-inch air space at top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Add warm water to cover.
Seal.
Let stand for 1 week. Strain free-flowing liquid through spigot and drink. Try it.

title: broiled london broil with purple plum sauce
directions: Score the steak quite deeply with a sharp knife all the way down its length on the diagonal, about every 1/2-inch.
Turn steak around and repeat, scoring in opposite direction, so score marks become little squares.

title: date bar dessert
directions: Prepare date bar mix as directed.
Let cool.
Crumble and mix in whipped cream.

title: bloody mary's for a crowd
directions: In large pitcher, combine all except lime or lemon slices; refrigerate to chill.
To serve, pour into tall glasses with ice cubes.
Top with lemon or lime slice.
Also, a stalk of celery may be added to each drink.

title: easy blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 8 to 9-inch baking dish. Add sugar to blackberries and lemon juice.
Let come to boil. Add muffin mix and milk.
Stir until well blended.
Spoon into baking pan with butter (don't stir).
Spoon hot blackberries and juice evenly over batter (do not stir).
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: batter for chicken("wing dings")
directions: Mix together and dip wings until completely covered.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: easy baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and pour into large baking dish.
Arrange pieces of chicken on top.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes, paprika and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours, uncovered, or until tender.
Add a bit more water if necessary; do not salt.
Soups have plenty of salt in them.
Serves 8.

title: wild rice shrimp bake
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package. In a large skillet, saute mushrooms, green peppers, onions and shrimp. Shrimp will turn pink. Add soup to the rice and stir. Add shrimp mixture to rice and soup. Stir and transfer to a well-greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with stuffing mix. Bake at 350° uncovered for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through. Serves 6.

title: chicken rice casserole(serves 4 to 8)
directions: Saute celery; add chicken and cook until chicken turns white, then brown.
Combine all ingredients to mix, except for cornflakes.
Place in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch greased baking dish. Sprinkle with cornflakes and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: congo squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Mix brown sugar, butter and eggs until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture; mix well. Add chips and pecans. Spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
Let stand for several minutes before cutting into squares.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Mix soups, onion, pepper, chili powder, garlic and tomatoes. In a buttered casserole, layer tortillas, layer chicken, layer soup and layer cheese.
Continue to layer in order until all ingredients are used, ending with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or plain.
Freezes well.

title: mock t-bone
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and blend with hamburger.
Shape into small t-bone 1 to 1 1/4-inch thick.
Douse with Worcestershire sauce on broiler pan.
Broil 5 minutes on each side.

title: creamy orange pie
directions: Combine crumbs and butter, press firmly on bottom and up side of 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.
In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy, gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then juice concentrate until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Garnish with fresh orange slices and whipping cream, if desired.
Store in refrigerator.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Beat egg, add buttermilk and mix.
Set aside.
Shake together flour, parsley, pepper and paprika.
In another bag, shake together cornflake crumbs and cheese.
Drop chicken in egg mixture, the flour mixture, back in egg mixture then the cornflake mixture. Take chicken and press down in cornflake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cake with fruit
directions: Mix ingredients.

Cook in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 350° and sprinkle with powdered sugar, or microwave in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch microwave dish for 8 1/2 minutes, turning 1/2 turn every 2 minutes, or place in Dutch oven with charcoal (9 on top and 9 on the bottom) and cook for 45 minutes (good on a campout).

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet. In separate pan, saute onion and green pepper in the margarine until tender.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti as directed on package and drain.
Put spaghetti in a shallow pan.
Add ground beef to drained sauteed onion and green pepper.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Pour on top of the spaghetti. Sprinkle top with Mozzarella cheese until lightly covered.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until cheese is lightly browned.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
You may add extra Ragu and Mozzarella cheese if needed.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini, onion and tomatoes in olive oil.
Add corn, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese. Cover with lid and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: easy anginetti cream puffs
directions: Prepare Anginetti cookies by slicing off tops (about half the cookie).
Set aside.
Drain crushed pineapple, leaving a little juice.
Mix whipped topping and cream cheese together in a bowl for about 1 minute at medium speed.
Add crushed pineapple and blend all three ingredients for about 1 minute at low speed.
Drop about a tablespoonful of filling onto the bottom of cookies and replace tops.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Filling should be enough to fill all of the cookies in a package.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Saute celery, green pepper, medium onions and garlic in 2 tablespoons bacon grease or margarine for 10 minutes.

title: poncho's jambalaya(240 servings)
directions: Total liquid for jambalaya should be 8 gallons, including sauces, soup and water.

title: chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Combine chocolates and 1/2 cup water; stir over low heat until thick and blended.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Beat egg yolks with 1/2 cup sugar until light.

Add chocolate mixture, salt and vanilla extract and cool in refrigerator to room temperature. Gradually beat 1/2 cup sugar into beaten whites; fold into chocolate mixture and pour into cooled pastry shell.
Chill until firm.
Whip the heavy cream until stiff and add 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract.
When ready to serve, use the heavy whipped cream as topping for the pie.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). In a 1-quart casserole dish, combine mushrooms, onion, garlic, green pepper, Italian seasoning, seasoning salt, pepper and parsley. Pour water and butter over mixture; cover. Bake in preheated oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add and mix the rest of the ingredients with the jello.
Chill until set.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.

title: russian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: dawn's frozen strawberry pie
directions: Blend Cool Whip, sweetened condensed milk and daiquiri mix together. I use mixer to make sure it is mixed well. Pour into pie shells and place in freezer.

title: baked eggs
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over bread. Top with butter.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandma's poultry dressing
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage.
Drain and discard the drippings. In a large mixing bowl, combine sausage and remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: crock-pot macaroni pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a crock-pot which has been greased with 2 tablespoons shortening.
Cut several strips of cheese and put on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour in a big bowl and pack down in middle, leaving a hole in middle.
Pour in milk and oil.
Mix with hand slowly until thick.
Then clean hand.
Flour hand and knead over dough until it is just stiff enough to pinch off and roll up in your hand.
Place on greased baking pan and pat down with melted margarine.
Bake at 450° to 500° until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove bones.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Use broth to prepare stuffing mix; set aside.
Heat together both cans of soup; pour over chicken.
Spoon stuffing mix over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking dish.
Crumble bread into crumbs.
Mix all ingredients; pour into baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients 2 or 3 times.
Put in bowl the egg plus enough milk to make 1/2 cup.
Beat and combine with dry ingredients.
Drop into liquid 1/2 tablespoon at a time.
Bake or cook 10 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Take a fork and punch a couple of holes in each one.
Place in baking dish.
Pour a bottle of Italian dressing over the chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with aluminum foil; marinate overnight. Bake at 350° until a golden brown (about 1 hour).

title: spinach salad
directions: There will be enough dressing for 2 salads.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; cook until thick.
Cool; pour over sliced strawberries in a cooked pie shell or a graham cracker crust.

title: meat sauce
directions: Mix flour, curry and mustard; blend into butter.
Add other ingredients; bring to boil and simmer 2 hours.
Serve over London Broil.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Saute sausage, celery, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Put in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add mushroom soup, chicken soup, wild rice, chicken broth, chestnuts, mushrooms and spices.
Mix and top with almonds.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick cinnamon bread snack
directions: Spread butter on bread slices.
Sprinkle on cinnamon and sugar.
Place in microwave and cook for 2 minutes on medium. Remove and roll them.
Enjoy with milk.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: *May also use 1/2 cup Cheez Whiz.

title: banana-pecan pie
directions: Mash half of the banana and cube the other half. Blend all the ingredients; pour into the pie shell. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes until crust is golden and filling is set. Let cool at least 2 hours before cutting.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients.
Add shrimp and crab meat.
Mix together spaghetti and serve warm.
Serve with Greek salad.

title: chocolate oatmeal chip cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. In large bowl, cream butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in Nestle milk chocolate morsels, oats and walnuts.

title: peach or strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch and boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in jello.
Place sliced fruit in a cooked pie crust.
Spoon mixture over fruit and chill for several hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Cut sweet potatoes in halves or quarters; place in baking dish.
In a small saucepan, bring to boil brown sugar, water, salt and butter.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: irish soda bread "aunt gussies"
directions: Sift together into a mixing bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in raisins and caraway seed with eggs, buttermilk and melted butter in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients and mix lightly.
Pour into greased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake at 375° for one hour or until done.

title: guacamole
directions: Blend all ingredients in a bowl with a beater until fairly smooth.
Amounts of salsa and sour cream may be increased to suit taste and/or to increase smoothness.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat sugar, corn syrup and milk to a boil on medium-high and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and butter.
Beat by hand until cool and pour onto buttered platter. Don't try to make fudge on a rainy day; it won't set properly.

title: poor mans almond roca
directions: Sprinkle nuts onto well greased pan.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Stir constantly for 7 minutes.
Pour mixture over nuts immediately.
Top with chopped chocolate.
Let chocolate melt; then spread over batter with a table knife.
Place pan in freezer about 20 minutes.
Then cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: main dish cabbage
directions: Brown onion and ground beef in skillet.
In a 1 1/2 quart casserole layer half the cabbage and half the ground beef; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Layer the other half cabbage and ground beef; again sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with tomato soup.
Bake, covered, in 350 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: hawiian spareribs
directions: Beat together eggs, flour, salt, and pepper.
Coat ribs with this batter and brown on all sides in fat.
Cover and cook slowly for 45 minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Stem and seed peppers and cut into one-inch squares.
Add peppers and pineapple to meat.
Cover and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Add enough water to reserved pineapple juice to make one cup liquid.
Mix cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar, vinegar, and pineapple liquid.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Pour over meat mixture and cook slowly for five minutes.
Serves three or four.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter casserole dish; arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onions, cheese and margarine.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and black pepper.
Pour cheese sauce over all; add more cheese if you like.
Sprinkle with generous amount of paprika.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 375°.
Remove cover and bake 15 more minutes.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding mix with corn syrup.
Gradually add evaporated milk and egg, stirring to blend.
Then add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° until top is firm and just begins to crack, about 40 minutes.
Cool at least 3 hours.

title: sinful salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine Jell-O and boiling water.
Stir with rubber spatula until Jell-O is completely dissolved.
Cool.
Add bananas, pecans, strawberries and pineapple to Jell-O, stir to combine.
Divide in half.
Pour half the Jell-O mixture into a 12 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate until set, about 1 hour, keeping remaining Jell-O at room temperature.
Spread sour cream or cream cheese evenly over set Jell-O.
Pour on remaining Jell-O.
Cover and refrigerate until set about 1 1/2 hours or overnight.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order listed except the cheese.
Pour half of the batter in greased baking dish then half the cheese sprinkled on the batter.
Add the rest of batter and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until done.

title: sweet potatoes with apples
directions: In a large saucepan, cover sweet potatoes with water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until just tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Alternate layers of potatoes and apples in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour orange juice over potatoes and apples. Mix brown sugar, ginger and cinnamon, then sprinkle over potatoes and apples.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: reuben chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking pan. Cover with sauerkraut.
Cover them with the dressing and sprinkle the cheese.
(I use the slices.)
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done in a 350° oven.

title: crystal cucumber pickle
directions: *Tie spice in cloth.

title: braised cabbage
directions: Saute green onions in melted butter in large skillet or wok until tender.
Add cabbage and carrots.
Saute 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Can use oil instead of butter, if desired.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in casserole dish.
Cook in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or microwave approximately 5 minutes.

title: peppermint candy
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add peppermint chips and mix well.
Have sheet of wax paper spread out.
After mixing chocolate and mint chips well, pour mixture onto wax paper as thick or as thin as you want.
Put in refrigerator for about 1 hour, then break into pieces.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients.
Heat to dissolve sugar and cool. Mash bananas well.
Stir in juices, bananas and cooled sugar mixture; mix well.
Divide mixture into 3 containers and freeze. One hour before serving, remove mixture from freezer.
Spoon into punch bowl and add 1 liter of ginger ale for each frozen container used.
Mix well.

title: taco dip
directions: Cut Velveeta into cubes and chop
onion.
Put all ingredients into a double boiler and cook until all cheese cubes are melted. Remove from heat.
Keep stirring until there is no film on top. Dip tortilla chips and enjoy.
Refrigerate when not using.
Can be served warm or cold.

title: heavenly ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve liquid.
Add cold water to liquid to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water to jello in large bowl.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate about 1 1/4 hours.
Stir in Cool Whip with whisk until smooth. Refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Stir in rest of ingredients and chill for about 4 hours.
Yields 10 servings.

title: blueberry supreme
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Fold cream cheese mixture into Dream Whip mixture; pour on cool crust.
Spread blueberries on top.
Let cool good; then enjoy.

title: steamed cabbage and smoked sausage
directions: Core and shred cabbage and wash well.
Cut sausage in 4 to 6 pieces, then slice down the center.
Place cabbage in large skillet.
Cover with just enough water to steam it, about 1 cup water.
Place sausage on top of cabbage.
Cover; cook over low heat until sausage is done and cabbage is tender.
Serves 4.

title: cinnamon twist bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Pour milk over sugar, salt and shortening; cool to lukewarm.
Beat in half of flour and beaten eggs.
Stir in yeast, raisins and rolled oats.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board. Knead until satiny, about 10 minutes.
Round dough into ball and place in greased bowl.
Cover.
Let rise until double or 1 hour. Divide dough into 2 parts.
Cover and let rest for 10 minutes.

title: hot chocolate fudge for ice cream topping
directions: Melt the oleo, salt and chocolate.
Stir in the condensed milk, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Bring to boil for a few minutes.

title: sweet and sour dressing(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and beat eggs slightly.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into an unbaked 8-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° until filling is firm.

title: parsley garlic rolls
directions: Coat a 12-c. muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray. In a small bowl, combine the melted butter, parsley, garlic, and salt; mix well. On a lightly floured surface, roll the bread dough into a 12 inch square. Spread the parsley mixture over the dough, leaving a 1/2 inch border on the top and bottom edges. Roll dough tightly, jelly roll fashion, starting at the bottom edge. Pinch to seal the edge. Cut the roll of dough into 1 inch wide slices. Place each slice flat side down into a cup of the muffin pan. Cover and let rise in a warm place for 1 hour, or until doubled in size. Preheat the oven to 400°. Bake the rolls for 9 to 11 minutes, or until golden. Remove from the pan and serve warm.

title: papaw's favorite cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening gradually.
Add 2/3 cup powdered sugar and flavoring, beating until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour and mix well.
Stir in chopped pecans.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Top Ramen and sugar, together in large bowl.
Break up the Top Ramen noodles, but don't cook. Mix the noodles with the sugar.
Toss into salad.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake and crumble small amount in bottom of tall glass bowl.
Layer pineapple, pudding and cherry pie filling; start over with rest of cake and layer again.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts, coconut and cherries.
Makes enough for large group.

title: kristie's jello cut outs
directions: Use cherry or strawberry flavored Jell-O for Christmas and Valentines; orange for Halloween and pineapple flavored for Easter. Use your choice of cookie cutters:
pumpkin, Christmas trees, rabbits, etc.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Add nuts just before serving.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill 9-inch pie pan 2/3 full of peeled and sliced apples. Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples. Mix together 1 cup sugar, flour, nuts, butter, vanilla and egg. Spoon this mixture over apples and pat down.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream to serve.

title: quick and easy spicy hot dogs
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 24 hours.
Transfer to a fondue pot and serve bubbling.
Recipe will feed several.

title: cold bread pudding
directions: Pour milk over biscuits; let set until milk is absorbed. Beat sugar, eggs and vanilla; add to bread mixture. Pour into a greased 3-quart baking dish. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: ham and cheese logs
directions: Have Cheddar cheese at room temperature.

title: bean soup
directions: *White beans or limas may be used.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° until it sets, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: leftover meat and rice casserole
directions: Brown onion in hot shortening; add meat and rice.
Cook slowly until rice is golden brown.
Add tomatoes, water and seasoning. Stir well and pour into greased casserole.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer. Serve at once from casserole.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In a medium saucepan, pour whole bottle of chili sauce and jar of grape jelly.
Over low heat, stir occasionally until jelly melts.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine meat, finely chopped onions, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Form into small balls and place in a deep baking dish.
Pour sauce mixture over meatballs, making sure all are covered.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: In casserole dish, place half of the potatoes, half the cheese and 1/2 the margarine.
Then add remaining potatoes, cheese and margarine.
Top with soup.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: low-fat burritos
directions: Cook chicken in a skillet until done.
Mix mayo, sour cream, cumin, mustard, salt and pepper. Stir and add chicken; mix.
Add shredded cheeses and mix.
Place 2 spoonfuls on a tortilla shell. Roll up and place in baking dish. Spoon salsa over and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: alabama rice
directions: Simmer ingredients in skillet 20 minutes.
Add consomme and water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir before serving.
Serves 4.

title: low-fat applesauce raisins drops
directions: Cream the margarine until fluffy.
Blend in brown sugar and egg.
Alternately add
sifted dry ingredients and applesauce. Blend well.
Stir in vanilla, oats and raisins.
Drop by tablespoons on nonstick cookie pan.
Flatten dough.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.
Cookies stay moist.

title: banana-raisin cookies(low-fat; no sugar except from fruit)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
(Batter should be a little stiff.)
Drop by teaspoon onto a nonstick or lightly greased cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake for about 15 minutes.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Put oatmeal into boiling water and let stand.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add oil; add oatmeal mixture and all other ingredients.
Mix well as you go along.
Add bread flour until you get a stiff workable dough.
Knead well.
Let rise.
Knead again and shape into loaves.
Let rise and bake at 350° until done (approximately 20 to 25 minutes).

title: no-knead wheat bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over lukewarm water.
Add 2 teaspoons honey. Leave to "work" while preparing dough.
Warm whole-wheat flour by placing in oven (250°) for 20 minutes.
Combine molasses with 2/3 cup water.
Combine yeast mixture with molasses mixture.
Stir this into warmed flour, add salt and wheat germ and finally 1 1/3 cups water.
(Dough will be sticky.)
Butter loaf pan.
Turn dough into pan.
Smooth dough in pan with spatula which has been held under cold water.
Sprinkle sesame seed over top of loaf.
Leave to rise to top of pan in warm, draft-free place.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until crust is brown and sides are firm.
Set pan on rack to cool for about 10 minutes, then remove.
Cool completely before serving.

title: pizza sandwiches
directions: Spread the butter on first; spread mixture on cut side of bread.
Place cut side up on baking sheet pan.
Top with thin slices of ripe tomatoes.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Top with 8 slices of cheese until melted, about 5 minutes.
Cut into 8 pieces.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Shape into balls; roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place Hershey's Kiss or star in center of each cookie while hot.
Serves 48.

title: butterscotch bars(unbaked)
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and butter in a saucepan.
Heat to a boiling point.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and marshmallows.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Melt chips and peanut butter at low speed. Add vanilla.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Refrigerate.
Cut into 3 dozen bars.

title: chili bake
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and beef; brown lightly.
Add tomatoes with juice to mixture in skillet.
Add kidney beans, chili powder, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Top with cornbread mixture and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon spiced walnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix walnuts with egg white until well coated and sticky to the touch.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over walnuts, tossing until sugar mixture completely coats walnuts.
Spread on ungreased baking sheet for 20 minutes, stirring once.
Cool.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 2 cups.

title: double chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.

title: green bean and potato delight
directions: Combine beans, potatoes, bacon grease and salt in pressure cooker.
Cook for 1 hour on medium-high heat.
Let steam escape before removing lid.
Simple and easy to prepare.

title: tan fudge
directions: Mix over stove the light brown sugar, sugar and butter.
Cook until it comes to a boil that can't be stirred down.
Cook an additional 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 (12 ounce) jar peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Stir and mix thoroughly. Pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: easy kielbasa bean soup
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, bring vegetables and water to boiling; reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add kielbasa and bean soup.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer thinly sliced potatoes, onion, frozen vegetables and chicken.
Pour in broth and soup. Cover with pie crust or biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate.
Add sugar and milk. Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and simmer to desired consistency.
Add 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir until melted. Frost cooled cake.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, water, salt, garlic salt, oregano and pepper in a large saucepan.
Cover; bring to a boil, then simmer until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.
Mash potatoes slightly.
Add milk and butter.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve.
Hm good.

title: golden hot milk cake
directions: Beat together the eggs, sugar and flour; mixture will be very thick.
Next, heat butter and milk together in microwave about 2 minutes.
Blend in the egg mixture; will become very soupy.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Can be used for sheet cake or cupcakes!!
Bake at 350° to 400° until toothpicks come out clean.

title: eggs benedict
directions: Follow directions on package of hollandaise sauce for the sauce. Heat slices of Canadian bacon. Poach eggs. Split open the muffins and toast them. Put English muffins on plate; place a piece of Canadian bacon on muffin; place poached egg over bacon (upside down); cover with sauce.

title: cow pies
directions: In a double boiler, over simmering water, melt the chocolate chips and shortening. Stir until smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in raisins and nuts. Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cheddar baked potatoes
directions: In small pan, mix soup, paprika and pepper (grease pan).
In 2-quart baking dish, arrange potatoes in overlapping rows (go around pan).
Sprinkle with cheese.
Spoon soup mixture over cheese.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and cool.
Mix stuffing, cheese and parsley together.
Dip boned chicken in melted butter and then in stuffing mix.
When all are coated, place in 9 x 12-inch dish or pan and sprinkle balance of stuffing mixture on top.
Drip small amount of butter on top, also.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put mixture in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out on floured board and cut like biscuits.
Bake at once for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: frozen cherry delight
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip. Add the pie filling and crushed pineapple. Pour into 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan and freeze. Cut into squares.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix with fork.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in a jelly roll cake pan.
Cool.
Frost with Bakery Frosting.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; whip at medium speed for 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour into crust.
Chill to set and serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine and melt cream cheese and soup.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir and chill to serve.

title: doughnuts(from inga's article on cookcars)
directions: Flour enough to handle easily, maybe 8 to 9 cups.
Lard piping hot.
The rolling pin was a great big log, real heavy, and the cookie cutter was a saucer.
The doughnuts were not rolled as thin as cookies.

title: grandma's easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in square or oblong baking pan in a 350° oven. Mix milk, flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
Pour into melted margarine; do not stir.
Add flavoring to 1 large can of fruit (or fresh or frozen, sweetened to taste).
Pour into dough; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until browned.
Very good!

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Slowly add sugar and egg yolk. Beat until fluffy.
Add flour and vanilla.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Gently press a pecan half or cherry in center of each ball.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 4 dozen.

title: boston cream cheese pie
directions: Grease bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package; pour batter evenly into spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Carefully place 2 cups water in a pot, then place pot on stove and cover.
Turn on heat to high.
Water is ready when bubbles form.

title: no bake skillet cookies
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients in a pan, stirring until smooth. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, coconut and oats.
Mix thoroughly. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Refrigerate.

title: hot spiced drink
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: quick brown sugar frosting
directions: Mix sugar, half and half and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Cool to lukewarm, then beat until creamy and thick enough to spread.
Add cream if it gets too thick.
Great for applesauce or spice cake.

title: no fat gazpacho salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl, tossing gently to mix. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.

title: hot dish
directions: Mix all together and cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn and sausage casserole
directions: * Turkey sausage may be used instead of pork sausage.

title: steamed vegetable platter(serves 4)
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, heat the oil and stir in the curry powder until blended.
Add the onions; when it's sizzling, add the broth and cabbage.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until slightly wilted, about 2 minutes.
Add more liquid if needed. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, an additional 6 minutes, until tender-crisp.
Sprinkle with peanuts and serve.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Melt shortening in soup kettle or Dutch oven.
Add the beef and cook slowly until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and stew until vegetables and rice are cooked.
